name: Mana
description: An orb of pure energy, a valuable resource.

name: Coal
description: A hard lump of coal, mined from deep within the earth.

name: Diamond
description: A person's best friend.

name: Iron Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Ruby
description: A marvelous red ruby, mined deep from within the earth.

name: Sapphire
description: A shiny blue sapphire, mined deep from within the earth.

name: Adamant Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Amethyst
description: A gorgeously purple amethyst, mined deep from within the earth.

name: Gold Ore
description: I've struck gold! I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Haunted Log
description: A log, haunted by the restless soul of a vengeful stump.

name: Pricklepop Pear
description: A sour pear covered in pointy thorns, no good for eating.

name: Squashed Banana
description: Not the worst thing to have thrown at you, at least.

name: Leafie's Leaf
description: It looks innocent, but its edges are dangerously sharp.

name: Bug Shell
description: It's just a shell, but it's harder than iron.

name: Hot Sauce
description: A Scorpepper's sting is searingly hot, owed all to heat of their saucey venom. Silver lining? It's the ultimate meal enhancer.

name: Prickletot Pear
description: A sour pear covered in pointy thorns, no good for eating.

name: Old Boot
description: This looks like it's been in the water for a long time, it's beyond repair now.

name: Potato
description: Potatoes are a starchy vegetable, perfect for dishes that fortify the body.

name: Wheat
description: Perfectly versatile; it can be turned into flour for people, or turned into feed for your farm animals.

name: Lettuce
description: A very mild flavor makes this vegetable excellent for pairing up with many different ingredients.

name: Tomato
description: If tomatoes are a fruit, does that make tomato soup a type of juice? The perfect question to ruminate on as you cook your meal.

name: Shimmeroot
description: Shimmering with flakes of gold, it's not hard to see where this root got its name.

name: Onion
description: The traditional ingredient of choice for a sweet, savory flavor in any dish. Just try not to cry when you cut them!

name: Carrot
description: Surprisingly high in sugar, carrots are a cornerstone of flavor in many different types of dishes.

name: Pepper
description: Some people argue that the spice is an acquired taste, but this fiery pepper is great for adding an edge to any dish.

name: Lightning in a Bottle
description: This was much easier to catch than you've been led to believe.

name: Copper Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Cow
description: Cows are a trusty farm staple that are a great source of milk.

name: Golden Milk
description: Liquid gold- literally! This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Mushroom
description: There's a fungus among us.

name: Seaweed
description: Even the sea has weeds.

name: Milk
description: Good for your bones.

name: Apple
description: Crisp, sweet and great at keeping the doctor away.

name: Orange
description: Used to grow only in the warm Southern Isles, but adapted quite well to a more northern climate.

name: Blueberry
description: They're definitely blue and most assuredly berries, so the name checks out.

name: Strawberry
description: Notoriously difficult to grow, these yummy little fruits only flourish in the most fertile of soil.

name: Rice
description: Full of starch, you may be surprised how filling these little grains can be.

name: Dorado
description: This fish is known for its power and speed, it can easily swim up to 60 miles per hour!

name: Crab
description: You'd be crabby too if someone reeled you in on a hook!

name: Sea Bass
description: What do you sea, bass?

name: Chromafin
description: Legends tell of a fish, said to have descended from the rainbows above, whose chromatic scales endlessly shift and change color.

name: Duorado
description: The fish with a face so nice it has it twice.

name: Shadow Tuna
description: The eggs of this shadowy fish are a favorite delicacy of Withergate's upper class.

name: Gold Boot
description: A boot of solid gold! One man's treasure is another man's... treasure?

name: Angelfin
description: Gliding through the waters with an unmatchable angelic grace, all it's missing is a chorus of trumpets.

name: Bubblefish
description: A mythical elemental fish that is impossible to see in the water. Angling this would truly be a feat worthy of songs.

name: Devilfin
description: Fishermen in Withergate go about their work in constant fear that they may be unlucky enough to meet the Devilfin on the end of their line.

name: Lobster
description: A Sun Haven favorite, townies are especially fond of drenching these guys in plenty of fresh butter.

name: Stone
description: A lump of ordinary rock, I bet it could be crafted into some sort of stonework.

name: Log
description: A hunk of hewn tree, just waiting to be turned into planks.

name: Sand Dollar
description: I wonder if this is what fish use as money?

name: Clam
description: This would go great in a nice chowder.

name: Black Fridge
description: The Great City produces all sorts of cutting edge industrial wonders.

name: Egg
description: It doesn't matter which came first, we're just happy they both showed up.

name: Chicken
description: Take good care of your chickens and you'll have all the eggs you ever need.

name: Golden Egg
description: Do you think the yolk is golden, too? This golden animal product will sell for a high price.

name: Wool
description: A bundle of pure wool, this animal product will sell for a fair price.

name: Sheep
description: Sheep actually rely on their caretakers to trim their wool. The sheep gets a haircut, you get the wool. It's a win-win!

name: Golden Wool
description: A bundle of pure golden wool, this golden animal product will sell for a high price.

name: Baby Stump
description: You never thought a stump could be adorable, but here we are.

name: Golden Log
description: Who needs gold leaf when you've got gold log? This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Silk
description: A soft sheet of silk, great for crafting.

name: Silk Moth
description: Maybe not your conventional farm animal, but these domesticated moths produce plenty of silk.

name: Golden Silk
description: Luxurious silk woven of pure gold. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Feather
description: The fledgling feathers of baby griffons are famously known for their softness.

name: Baby Griffon
description: Adult griffons make for ferocious beasts, but baby griffons make for cute little companions.

name: Golden Feather
description: Solid gold, yet no heavier than a normal feather. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Peanuts
description: Coveted by squirrels, these shelled nuts are often left behind as gifts to those who have befriended the furry critters.

name: Dragon Scale
description: Though comparatively tiny compared to a scale from a fully grown dragon, it's still harder than mithril.

name: Earth Crystal
description: The elemental force of earth, hardened into a crystal.

name: Water Crystal
description: The elemental force of water, hardened into a crystal.

name: Fire Crystal
description: The elemental force of fire, hardened into a crystal.

name: Sparkling Dust
description: Shiny flakes of rock and crystal left behind by the passing of wind sprites, Nel'Varians love using it to add sparkle to their creations.

name: Cat Nip
description: Cats usually keep this potent herb safely guarded, though they are known to drop some when excited.

name: Werewolf
description: Wolves once stalked the forest marshes, until these apex predators were exposed to dark, otherworldly magic. These 'werewolves' are especially clever, scavenging all sorts of things for their keepers.

name: Pig
description: Pigs are actually very intelligent and sociable creatures, able to keep other farm animals happy. In their down time, pigs are even known to forage for earth crystals.

name: Golden Berry
description: A shiny golden berry. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Berry
description: A common berry, found almost everywhere in the forests.

name: Snaccoon
description: A very, very big friend for your farm! This snaccoon has come to visit and will earn his keep by sharing snacks with you each day.

name: Ramberry Bush
description: One day, long ago, a Nel'Varian enchanter looked at a bush and said 'Hey, that kind of looks like a ram'. The rest is history. These cuddly ram bushes produce berries.

name: Mooshroom Cow
description: Wayward bovine sometimes found themselves wandering into the Elven forest, in search of pastures to graze in. The mana there manipulated them in... odd ways. Now, they produce mushrooms!

name: Golden Mushroom
description: A shiny golden mushroom. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Fire Rune
description: A magical sealing rune, containing the element of fire.

name: Golden Fire Rune
description: A shiny golden fire rune. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Baby Phoenix
description: Phoenixes are beautiful and legendary creatures, though they take thousands of years to mature! In the meantime, they often scavenge fire runes for their keepers.

name: Golden Earth Rune
description: A shiny golden earth rune. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Fae Fox
description: Nel'Varians have lived in tandem with their forest foxes for countless generations. Many of them can be tamed, their sensitive noses capable of detecting buried earth runes.

name: Earth Rune
description: A magical sealing rune, containing the element of earth.

name: Golden Water Rune
description: A shiny golden water rune. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Fishfrog
description: It's like a... fish... imp... frog... thing? Whatever it is, they're friendly farm companions and love to dive to the depths of pools in search of water runes.

name: Water Rune
description: A magical sealing rune, containing the element of water.

name: Unrefined Metal
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Metallic Dragon
description: Dragons often consume rock, to help harden their scales. Metallic dragons have eaten far too much iron, and have hardened their scales to iron! They often shed unrefined metal.

name: Golden Sand
description: Shiny golden sand. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Sandworm
description: Native originally to the deserts of the Eastern Region, these worms found a new home in Withergate as the growing city was always in need of sand for use in construction. Hence, they're an excellent source of sand!

name: Sand
description: Normal castles are built of stone and wood, but legendary castles are built from sand.

name: Unrefined Concrete
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Cement Slime
description: Slimes are versatile and adaptable. If it's a viscous liquid, a slime has embodied it. This guy, for example, literally drips Withergate concrete.

name: Slime Ink
description: Sticky slime that leaves behind a dark stain on whatever it touches.

name: Golden Slime Ink
description: Shiny golden slime. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Tar Slime
description: An especially thick slime of dark, bubbling tar. Fun fact: they produce slime ink, which was ingeniously utilized by Xyla for printing Withergate's ticket currency. Not fun fact: Counterfeiters figured this out years ago.

name: Crystal Bat
description: Unlike other bats, the crystal bat has excellent eyesight. They love to scavenge for stones and shiny rocks - but most of all, they love to scavanage glorite.

name: Spooky Silk
description: As silky as it is spooky, or perhaps as spooky as it is silky.

name: Golden Spooky Silk
description: Shiny golden spooky silk. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Silk Wyrm
description: Some dragons breath fire. Others breath torrents of water, storms of ice or even blasts of electricity. This little wyrm breathes spooky silk. That's right, spooky silk.

name: Mimic
description: The stories you've heard of mimics gobbling up unsuspecting treasure hunters are all myths. These goofy guys only want to gobble up spare change they find, sometimes belching up the bounties for their keepers.

name: Slime Goop
description: This goop is icky and sticky, gross!

name: Ooey
description: A slimey little fella who decided to live with you on your farm. Is good at sliming up soil into slime goop.

name: Buppy
description: Who's a good doggy?

name: Kitty
description: Here kitty, kitty.

name: Bunny
description: No matter where you go, your bunny buddy will be sure to hop dutifully behind you.

name: Prince Frog
description: Grant your farm the grace of amphibian aristocracy.

name: Shiver
description: Normally at home in the frigid Northern Region, this happy penguin is cool with going anywhere!

name: Bubbles
description: Might look a little scary, but it just wants to be your friend!

name: Smolder
description: A cute little flame sprite, just be careful trying to pet it!

name: Nimbus
description: Gale essence formed together to make this cuddly little buddy just for you.

name: Grimbus
description: Not all clouds are happy, but he's still pretty cute!

name: Baby Tiger
description: This tiny tiger cub can't wait to be your new best friend!

name: Baby Dragon
description: A hatchling dragon, befriended only by those most worthy.

name: Unicorn
description: A tiny unicorn friend to accompany you on your adventures.

name: Blueberry Sprinkles
description: Apparently pets come in flavors, who knew?

name: Mister Slither
description: I shall call him Missster Slither.

name: Raccoon
description: It's a sneaky little raccoon.

name: Chocolate Sprinkles
description: Apparently pets come in flavors, who knew?

name: Mint Sprinkles
description: Apparently pets come in flavors, who knew?

name: Kit
description: A mischievous little fox ready to tag along on your adventures.

name: Percy
description: Hoo's your buddy? Percy is, that's hoo!

name: Strawberry Sprinkles
description: Apparently pets come in flavors, who knew?

name: Striped Mister Slither
description: I shall call him Missster Slither.

name: Black Kitty
description: Here kitty, kitty.

name: Black Unicorn
description: A tiny unicorn friend to accompany you on your adventures.

name: Weedy
description: A little weed sprout monster, it seems convinced that you're super fun to be around.

name: Pebbles
description: A tiny shard left behind by the elemental monster Krusty. This friendly little guy is definitely not a chip off the old rock.

name: Lantern Spirit
description: With an affinity for taking care of plants, this little dragon has a chance to water some of your crops when left on your farm over night!

name: Dizzlette
description: Aw, it's a little baby Dizzy. Maybe with a little tender, love, and care this one won't grow up to be an earthquake-causing monster.

name: Hermy
description: Oh, a small white... squid? You're not sure if it's trying to hug you or eat you, but he sure is cute!

name: Grumbles
description: Oh, that hungry slime left behind a smaller slime. And it wants to stay with you. How... nice?

name: Prince Slimius VXXIII
description: The crown prince of slime, prepared to travel the world with you to gain kingly wisdom.

name: Bloom
description: A budding Spring fairy ready to tag along on your adventures.

name: Shortcake
description: A sweet little Summer whale ready to tag along on your adventures.

name: Rustle
description: A fun Fall friend ready to tag along on your adventures.

name: Brrrr-y
description: A bear-y chill Winter friend ready to tag along on your adventures.

name: Wizard Toad
description: This dark wizard accidentally turned himself into a toad. Making the best of the situation, he now works as a professional pet.

name: Witch Cat
description: Which kitty is the cutest? This one!

name: Rexxie
description: A tiny baby dinosaur, it was hatched from a dinosaur egg treated with a little chronomagic.

name: Walk Choy Pet
description: This happy little Walk Choy didn't feel like wandering away, he'd rather follow you!

name: Shiiwalki Mushroom Pet
description: Aw, this Shiiwalki Mushroom thinks you're a fun-guy and wants to follow you!

name: Grey Kitty
description: Here kitty, kitty.

description: Here kitty, kitty.

description: Apparently pets come in flavors, who knew?

description: Apparently pets come in flavors, who knew?

name: Audrey
description: Feed her!

name: Draco
description: A wyrm, kind of like a dragon without legs. This one is small enough to be a pet!

name: Jad
description: Fun fact: the sting of a manticore is enough to petrify a fully grown dragon. So, uh, just... never get stung.

name: Leechums
description: The leeches of Withergate are large, ravenous and surprisingly cuddly.

name: Octonot
description: Just keep him well fed and no one gets suction cupped.

name: Skerbs
description: Life at the bottom of the deep sea isn't all it's cracked up to be. Being a pet is much better!

name: Brimmy
description: Imps are feral and bitey little critters, often following in the footsteps of Demons. They respect only the most powerful of pet keepers.

name: Webster
description: It is notoriously difficult to learn how to safely keep a Witherwidow as a pet, they are reserved only for the most accomplished pet owners.

name: Nevermore
description: Crows are very intelligent birds - they also hold a grudge, so mind yourself around this pet!

name: Noire
description: Demons long regarded themselves as the most cold and calculating beings in the universe... and then they met cats.

name: Fangy
description: Heatvipers weren't native to the swamps of Withergate, but when Demon King Aster learned of the species, he quickly arranged the import of hundreds of the ferocious creatures.

name: Pips
description: Fae spirits are incredibly elusive, revealing their physical forms only to those they feel they can truly trust.

name: Chipper
description: Squirrelbears are... well, they're kind of like squirrels... but they're also like bears... well, anyways - they're super cute!

name: Pinkadee
description: Forest rocs are behemoth birds, nearly as large as dragons. Except this one. She's just little, and pink.

name: Ursil
description: Children are often seen gazing up at the sky, hoping to catch a glimpse of the storied cloud bears as they waft across the blue heavens.

name: Sweetie
description: A chromatic salamander, found underneath the ends of rainbows.

name: Buffo
description: Toads make great pets if you're lazy. All they want to do is sleep and eat!

name: Grimmy
description: Wait... why does he have that scythe? And why is he looking at you like that?!

name: Ollie
description: I didn't know Axolotls could walk... that might just be a Withergate thing.

name: Spoops
description: Not every ghost wants to spook the living. Some just want to be your friend.

name: Beelsie
description: This chunky little trickster's interests include burning brimstone and eating cupcakes.

name: Crumble
description: Gargoyles have followed Demons for as long as anyone can remember. This one would love to follow you!

name: Hubie
description: Withergate citizens are torn on the subject of cockatrice: are they cute pets, or city pests?

name: Kernie
description: A walking bag of popcorn! Butter not included.

name: Zeb
description:
Withergate Gremlins are gauranteed to NEVER* bite!

*Most of the time

name: Cornelius
description: This is one piece of candy that is friend, not food.

name: Tribert
description: Chimera's prove that three heads are better (and more expensive to feed) than one.

name: Jackie
description: Never look a jack rabbit directly in the eyes - those little antlers aren't just for show!

name: Vix
description: Foxes are elusive and aloof. One must earn their trust.

name: Griffith
description: The griffon of the Eastern Region are famous for their majestic 'bald' heads of white feather.

name: Dean
description: A cute little raptor from the Southern Isles! Just watch your toes around this one...

name: Kappy
description: Ships from across the Eastern Sea brought two unintended stowaways: rats... and kappas!

name: Zippy
description: At home in the highest clouds, pegasus are just as happy to chill out on an earthbound farm.

name: Mimi
description: Mimics are shapeshifting monsters that lure in and devour unwitting adventurers. Well, not this one. This one just wants to slobber all over you.

name: Bucky
description: A bucket full of friendship! Literally!

name: Orville
description: Winter owls are excellent hunters - they're also great pets!

name: Woodie
description: An enchanted wooden unicorn, snuggle away - but watch for splinters!

name: Tilia
description: The tree guardians are giant, mighty protectors of Nel'Vari... well, except for this one. She's too small!

name: Axie
description: Axolotl' is a Nel'Varian word, it means 'weird looking lizard'.

name: Myrtle
description: Don't mistake this little slug for a patch of moss!

name: Gus
description: Fungi come in all sorts of wonderful shapes and sizes. Except for Gus. He's just Gus-shaped.

name: Sizzle
description: Elementi come in all shapes as sizes, from ferocious rock beasts... to teeny little sparks of flame.

name: Bartleby
description: He's a chill fellow, so long as you don't try pulling him from his pot.

name: Revi
description: Hailing from the jagged cliffs of the Magma Isles, the phoenix bird is exotic and beautiful.

name: Pix
description: Pixies can be quite the troublemakers, so keep an eye on this one!

name: Kelsie
description: Kelpie are river spirits that appear before the morning mists dissipate. But are all of them THIS cute?

name: Pud
description: He can't see so good, so walk slow!

name: Wixxy
description: The fairy birds of Nel'Vari are often kept as pets, their songs make for great entertainment.

name: Graggle
description: Someone took the concept of a pet rock a bit too literally.

name: Pet Leash
description: Take your little friend for a stroll around the farm, or anywhere else! Leashes a pet to make it follow you.

name: Animal Food
description: A special blend, formulated for every type of farm animal.

name: Animal Name Tag
description: This special tag that can be used to give your pets and barn animals a name of their own.

name: Animal Feeder
description: Auto feed animals.

name: Gayle
description: She isn't the quickest pet, but she'll try her best.

name: Darter
description: Don't worry, these frogs aren't poisonous. They're actually venomous!

name: Grubby
description: This chubby grub loves making a home in rocky sand. Your farm isn't half bad, either.

name: Spirix
description: Dragon sprites are a very popular pet in Nel'Vari, just look at how beautiful they are. It's not hard to see why!

name: Booshroom

description: A tiny fae spirit who wanted to brave the physical realm, he'll stick with you for now.

name: Slash
description: A grungy little rat who only wants to do two things: Rock, and Roll.

name: QU4CK
description: A starter companion byteduck, this one is affectionally dubbed codename: QU4CK.

name: MOUS3
description: A bytemouse with custom programming implanted into its neuro-frame, it doesn't know what to do without bytes to nibble on, so it'll stick to following you.

name: Ellis
description: A lifelike hologram of Tech Acadamia, primary rival of the Cyber Acadamia. GO BYTES!

name: Lewey
description: A lifelike hologram of the Cyber Acadamia's current mascot, Lewey. GO CYBERS!

name: Daydream
description: This little dream ram lost their way to dreamland! They'll follow you around in the meantime.

name: Funky
description: Who doesn't want a monkey pal to run around with them?

name: Snoodles
description: A very exotic pet from the deep Elven Forests. Who knew a walking bush could be so cute and cuddly?

name: Roary
description: An exotic scorchmane cub from the Eastern Desert. Natural apex predators and extremely powerful... after they grow up, at least!

name: Leo
description: An exotic black scorchmane cub from the Eastern Desert. Natural apex predators and extremely powerful... after they grow up, at least!

name: Newton
description: Salamanders are very exotic highly adaptable critters. This one comes from the molten beaches of the Magma Isles, for instance.

name: Phillip
description: Salamanders are very exotic and highly adaptable critters. This one comes from the frigid plains of the Northern Region, for instance.

name: Celesti
description: Most celestial creatures encountered are primordial and violent beasts. But others, like this one, are cute little buddies.

name: Twinkle
description: A rabbit-squirrel-marshmallow thingy that was found at the very center of a distant galaxy. Not only super friendly and cute, but also a great face for mascot branding.

name: Friend Bot 1000
description: FRIENDSHIP FILE: FOUND. LOADING "FRIENDS FOREVER" PROTOCOL.

name: Grimble
description: A tiny yeti cub from the harsh Northern Region wilderness. He's looking for food, and you look like you know where to get it.

name: Joe Snow
description: A little bit of winter magic (along with some normal, non-winter magic) has brought this little snow dude to life!

name: Mistletoe
description: You're not sure if this is an Elf or a toy, but this little guy is just here to make toys and have a good time.

name: Sugardrop
description: He's a gummy, not a dummy. Be his friend!

name: Harmony
description: Every idol group needs a good mascot, and there are none cuter than this styling pup.

name: Gumbo
description: Normally more at home at the bottom of the sea, this dopey little guy is happy to tag along with you anywhere.

name: Angie
description: Funny, she doesn't look much like any Angel you've seen before. Oh well!

name: Charles
description: Charles is a cucumber. From the sea. A sort of 'sea cucumber', if you will.

name: Jiggles
description: He's not jelly, and he's not a fish... But he IS a friend!

name: Apollo
description: Born from the distant twinkles of primordial stars, this little ram has come a long way to be your friend.

name: Beezy Buzz
description: The Curators brought back many live specimens from Iseron. They had very little luck taming this angry little fly - maybe you'd like to give it a try?

name: Bingle
description: The Curators gave up trying to understand what sort of creature this little fellow is. Maybe you could study it as it follows you about?

name: Fido
description: He may not be a real dog, but he's still full of love (and cotton stuffing)!

name: Q't
description: The darkness-spawn of an ancient, powerful minion of O'aj'loza, the Burning Star and city of the dark. Letting it follow you around is probably a really bad idea... but the little guy is just so cute!

name: Leafel
description: A very exotic pet from the deep Elven Forests. Who knew a walking bush could be so cute and cuddly?

name: Origins of the Grand Tree and Nivara, Book I
description: An ancient tome, buried for countless ages. It looks Angelic in origin.

name: Origins of the Grand Tree and Nivara, Book II
description: An ancient tome, buried for countless ages. It looks Angelic in origin.

description: An ancient tome, buried for countless ages. It looks Angelic in origin.

name: Moo Potion
description: A white potion. Oh wait, no, it's just milk. Magic, potiony milk.

name: Cluck Potion
description: A potion with the creamy color of fresh eggshells. Will it make you lay an egg?

name: Leafy Potion
description: A deep green potion, the same color of the leaves. Probably tastes like leaves, too...

name: Centipede Potion
description: A centipede potion? Is there anything they WON'T make a potion out of these days?

name: Scorched Potion
description: This sizzling crimson potion looks like it puts even the hottest of sauces to shame.

name: Mild Pinchy Potion
description: 'Mild' makes sense, but how exactly can a potion be described as 'pinchy'? Drink it and find out!

name: Spicy Pinchy Potion
description: Prefer a pinch more spice in your transformation potions?

name: Banana Potion
description: This potion sort of looks like a banana smoothie. Maybe it'll taste like one too?

name: Torto Potion
description: The coloration of this potion is difficult to describe. Flat and monotone like a stone, yet shiny and reflective, almost like a turtle shell...

name: Cactus Potion
description: A watery green potion. It smells strongly of cactus flowers.

name: Magma Potion
description: Whew, this potion is almost too hot to handle. It also looks suspiciously like lava...

name: Ice Cube Potion
description: It's a bottle with a giant ice cube in it. The name checks out, at least.

name: Windmill Potion
description: A potion the color of sun faded wood. Even without being touched, the liquid inside the bottle swirls around and around and around...

name: Rock Potion
description: This potion ROCKS! Literally. It turns you into a rock. That's why it's called a rock potion.

name: Bush Potion
description: A box used to be considered the stealthiest of items, but no one expects the bush!

name: Lamp Potion
description: Always wanted to be a street lamp when you grew up? Then do we have the potion for you.

name: Bench Potion
description: Sometimes you just want to sit on a bench and enjoy the sunset... but what if you were the bench?

name: Tree Potion
description: If you didn't know any better, you'd say this potion looked an awful lot like apple juice.

name: Cut Stump Potion
description: Use potion, become stump. The perfect plan.

name: Stool Potion
description: "Better to be a stool than a fool", or at least that's what this potion's tag says.

name: Adventurer's Barrel Potion
description: Ever needed to look sharp? Then this is the potion for you.

name: Garden Barrel Potion
description: Looks like a typical potion, but it smells like a bundle of freshly cut flowers.

name: Dummy Potion
description: A potion the color of hay. Being a dummy has never been easier thanks to this transformation brew.

name: Pointing Potion
description: The perfect potion for those who never want to lose their direction in life.

name: Camping Potion
description: Thankfully this potion smells of burning logs and melting marshmallows, instead of the inside of a tent or something.

name: Delicious Potion
description: The name seems to fit the potion, this looks absolutely delicious to drink.

name: Picnic Potion
description: Best kept away from any ant potions.

name: Chest Potion
description: The real treasure inside this chest is you.

name: Purr-fect Potion
description: A brilliant white potion, almost like milk. It smells faintly of tuna and catnip.

name: Penguin Potion
description: A white and black potion that is perpetually chilly to the touch. It looks like it might taste pretty good.

name: Bunny Potion
description: A white potion with only the faintest hint of pink. It strangely seems as if it would taste of carrots.

name: Rainbow Potion
description: A sparkling potion that constantly shifts between all the colors of the rainbow. Does it taste like rainbows, too?

name: Puppy Potion
description: The potion practically shakes within its bottle as if too excitable to be contained. It smells like... puppy breath.

name: Merchant Potion
description: A rich purple potion. It sounds just like a coin purse if you shake it around.

name: Archmage Potion
description: A fiery red potion. It's sealed with a dab of wax stamped with Sun Haven's crest.

name: Apprentice Potion
description: A mellow orange potion. It smells like the inside of a well-used forge, but it's kind of nice.

name: Doctor Potion
description: A smooth grey potion. It smells like popsicle sticks and cotton balls.

name: Witch Potion
description: A vibrant purple potion. Something about it seems like it'd be great to water plants with.

name: Baker Potion
description: A soft brown potion. Smells like baking bread, with just a hint of stuffed animals.

name: Teacher Potion
description: A shimmering blue potion. If you swirl it around, the blue fades into a black that reminds you oddly of moonlight.

name: Nya Potion
description: A blindingly pink potion. Warning: Drinking this potion will result in the uncontrollable urge to say 'nya'.

name: Enchantress Potion
description: A cool yellow potion. Even for a potion, it seems to glimmer with extra enchantments.

name: Air Mage Potion
description: A bubbly orange potion. If it isn't kept weighted down to the ground, it'll float right away.

name: Knight Potion
description: A deep brown potion. If honor had a smell, this potion just might be it.

name: Spirit Fox Potion
description: A potion of ethereal blue color. The bottle is tightly sealed, yet a wispy smoke still escapes from within it.

name: Silk Potion
description: A potion that seems extra silky smooth. A soft powder floats into and out of the pale liquid inside the bottle.

name: Feather Potion
description: An earthy brown potion that smells a bit like the inside of a nest. Or at least what you'd imagine the inside of a nest must smell like.

name: Stump Potion
description: A woody brown potion, despite being a liquid it somehow seems to have the texture of tree bark.

name: Snake Oil Potion
description: A potion of a deep, menacing hue. Seems a bit viscous, more like an oil than a potion.

name: Peanut Potion
description: A peanut shell-colored potion. For some reason, you feel as if it'd pair nicely with a few acorns or walnuts.

name: Wild Potion
description: A slightly cloudy potion, it swirls and bubbles from within its bottle. It smells of wild and untamed forests.

name: Dragon Potion
description: White and cool in color, but this potion is very much warm in your hands.

name: Elven Lamp Potion
description: A strange orangish-yellowish potion. It emits a good amount of light.

name: Deer Potion
description: A thick brown potion, it gives off a strange aura of forest grace.

name: Slithery Potion
description: A thick black potion with bands of creamy white. It emits a curious hissing sound when shaken.

name: Bad Luck Potion
description: A thin, ink-like potion that gives off a strange and foreboding vibe. The name is just a fun little joke... right?

name: Galaxy Potion
description: A deeply dark potion filled with distant twinkles of stars. Despite being so dark it seems to radiate a bit of light.

name: Fiery Potion
description: Less of a potion and more of a bottle of fire. Drinking this might be a little tricky.

name: Ice Cream Potion
description: Super thick and super pink, if it wasn't labeled as a potion you might think it was just melted ice cream.

name: Shark Potion
description: A grey potion of somewhat gritty consistency. Bound to transform you into a huge vicious shark... or at least a small cute one.

name: Adventurer Potion
description: A wild blue potion. If you had to hazard a guess, you'd say it probably tastes just like meat.

name: Prince Potion
description: A royally red potion. It shines in the light as resplendently as any crown jewel.

name: Queen Potion
description: A hot pink potion. It's just a potion, yet it somehow gives off an aura that makes you feel inferior in its presence.

name: Vampire Potion
description: A somber yellow potion. Even just staring into the swirling liquid makes you feel like sitting down at a piano.

name: Undead Tree Potion
description: A muddy potion that looks as if it has bits of twig and dead leaves floating about in it. It'd take a bit of bravery, or at least boldness, to drink this down.

name: Bookworm Potion
description: A potion supposedly distilled from the plasm of a certain type of spectre. Well, bottoms up?

name: Tablecloth Potion
description: A potion of swirling shadows, you could swear for a brief moment you spotted a pair of white eyes gleaming at you from inside the bottle.

name: Static Potion
description: A potion that... wait... what's that sound? Is that... TV static? From the potion? Weird.

name: Tombstone Potion
description: This potion looks like someone liquified a rock. If spooky forests had a smell, this potion would totally be it.

name: Cheesy Slime Potion
description: An extra thick potion that sloshes slowly around in its bottle. It certainly smells plenty cheesy.

name: Spooky Slime Potion
description: Orange and gooey, this potion seems a lot more like slime than anything else.

name: Sweet Slime Potion
description: A sweet looking pink potion, it seems a bit slime-like but is oddly no less appetizing.

name: Assistant's Potion
description: A leaf-green potion. It looks a tad viscous, like it might be hard to swallow. Hmph!

name: Saltwater Potion
description: A dark and murky potion, mixed with a ladleful of saltwater. Good luck ever forgetting what THIS potion tastes like!

name: Assassin's Potion
description: A nutty aroma with an ever-so-slight hint of rusty dagger. It probably tastes as odd as it smells.

name: Angelic Potion
description: A perfectly white potion, topped with a tiny floaty halo. How cute!

name: Swordsman Potion
description: A vibrantly orange potion, striped with streaks of black... It smells like honor.

name: Attendant Potion
description: A moon-shaped potion that twinkles with the dim shimmer of a lonely forest night.

name: Sharkskin Potion
description: Swirly, like ocean water. Bumpy, like sharkskin. Oh well! Bottom's up!

name: Corsair Potion
description: A potion brined in sea water... It looks like it's VERY sour.

name: Sun Haven Quilt
description: Sun Haven? More like Quilt Haven!

name: Knitted Socks
description: Perhaps the most classic thing to make on a loom... if it wasn't for scarves.

name: Scarf
description: It's like a necktie, only a lot more comfy.

name: Throw Blanket
description: Despite the name, you shouldn't throw blankets.

name: Elios Blanket
description: A blanket bearing the image of Elios, Sun Dragon.

name: Aerodynamic Helmet
description: A helmet of fine griffon feathers, this armor reduces air resistance and allows its wearer to strike with great force and accuracy.

name: Aerodynamic Chest Plate
description: A chestpiece of fine griffon feathers, this armor reduces air resistance and allows its wearer to strike with great force and accuracy.

name: Warcaster's Robe
description: Standard issue within the illustrious Warcaster corps of the Great Army. The crystals set within the jet black robes act as a magnifier for magic, increasing spell potency.

name: Aerodynamic Plate Legs
description: Leggings of fine griffon feathers, this armor reduces air resistance and allows its wearer to strike with great force and accuracy.

name: Aerodynamic Wings
description: A cloak of fine griffon feathers, this armor reduces air resistance and allows its wearer to strike with great force and accuracy.

name: Ruby Amulet
description: A beautifully carved ruby set on a golden chain, it increases vitality when worn.

name: Amulet of Immortality
description: A delicate amulet hanging by a thin golden chain, it preserves the life of its wearer. Increases the invulnerability period by 25% after taking damage.

name: Hear's Help Amulet
description: A strange amulet the likes of which you've never seen before. It senses its wearer's life force and emits a healing effect when it detects dangerously low levels.

name: Heart Amulet
description: A ruby heart has been set in this golden amulet, it increases vitality when worn.

name: Hungry Adventurer's Amulet
description: A ceremonial fork worn on a linen chain, no better accessory is there for declaring one's affinity for food.

name: Amulet of Time
description: A pocketwatch on a silver chain, enchanted with incredibly strong chronomancy. Its wearer can slip through time, controlling the outcome of battles.

name: Traveler's Silver Amulet
description: A silver amulet that has been passed down from one traveler to the next, fortune and vigor smile upon the one who possesses it.

name: Diamond Amulet
description: A piece of carved diamond, hymns and mantras have been placed on it to impart protection and endurance.

name: Rusted Amulet
description: Rusted from untold ages spent under water, at least it isn't the WORST thing you could find in a birdbath...

name: Candy Necklace
description: A necklace of candy gems, woven by an artistic Monsterfolk. Is it meant to frighten enemies, or just look stylish?

name: Brinestone Helm
description: Jabbu is lazy, but careful and clever. Well-armed soldiers keep the Boss in charge.

name: Brinestone Chest
description: Heavy armor enchanted with strange and alien-looking runes that enhance magical potency.

name: Brinestone Legs
description: You've never seen anything quite like the runes that are inscribed upon these leggings. They promise to increase magical might, yet it feels like the power may come with a price.

name: Brinestone Gauntlets
description: Faintly glowing runes burn on each knuckle of the gauntlets. Power? Most certainly. Worth it? Eh, probably...

name: Bush Helmet
description: A helmet formed from leaves and wood, it increases one's combat capabilities when worn and is the favored equipment of scouts and spies.

name: Bush Chest
description: A chestpiece formed from leaves and wood, it increases one's combat capabilities when worn and is the favored equipment of scouts and spies.

name: Bush Pants
description: Leggings formed from leaves and wood, it increases one's combat capabilities when worn and is the favored equipment of scouts and spies.

name: Bush Gloves
description: Gauntlets formed from leaves and wood, it increases one's combat capabilities when worn and is the favored equipment of scouts and spies.

name: Fall Helmet
description: Monsterfolk armor is rarely designed with practicality in mind, but none can doubt its strength and resilience. No wonder other races sometimes use it for themselves.

name: Fall Legs
description: Monsterfolk armor is rarely designed with practicality in mind, but none can doubt its strength and resilience. No wonder other races sometimes use it for themselves.

name: Fall Gloves
description: Monsterfolk armor is rarely designed with practicality in mind, but none can doubt its strength and resilience. No wonder other races sometimes use it for themselves.

name: Fathomancer's Crown
description: A salt-crusted helm adorned with shimmering branches of fathom coral. Weighing heavy on the head, this crown begs the question: What, exactly, would you trade for power?

name: Fall Chest Plate
description: Monsterfolk armor is rarely designed with practicality in mind, but none can doubt its strength and resilience. No wonder other races sometimes use it for themselves.

name: Fathomancer's Robe
description: In the darkest deeps, coral reefs grow on massive undersea deposits of Glorite. The magical properties of the coral are utilized in powerful vestments such as this.

name: Fathomancer's Leggings
description: One of the rarest and most powerful of the deep ocean's bounties, fathom coral teems with power. It also makes nice pants.

name: Fathomancer's Gloves
description: Constructed out of a strange material and embedded with tiny fragments of fathom coral to increase magical potency.

name: Fathomancer's Cape
description: Great power can be found in the deep fathoms, but be wary - bereft of light, you may not realize what you've lost in the dark.

name: Magic Gloves
description: Show off your affinity for all things magic with these stylish gloves.

name: Elven Gloves
description: Gloves of sophisticated Elven make.

name: Forest Hunter's Gloves
description: Stretched and smoothed fabric gloves, totally silent as the hunter stalks their prey.

name: Spark Gloves
description: Padded fabric gloves, they give the fingers extra protection against prolonged use of magic from your fingertips.

name: Claw Gloves
description: Claws need gloves, too.

name: Slime Gloves
description: Gloves covered in an infinite coating of slime. How... nice?

name: Golden Feather Winged Cape
description: A cape of golden feathers, each shining quill catches the light in a dazzling flash.

name: Golden Silk Scarf
description: A massive golden scarf fit for the very gods... For someone of your stature, it'll work perfect as a cape.

name: Golden Spooky Silk Robes
description: Spun from golden spooky silk, these robes are both gilded gold and perfectly spooky.

name: Golden Ram Horns
description: Ancient legends tell of shining golden horns, and that the one who wears them upon their head shall look super mega cool.

name: Golden Gloves
description: Exactly what one needs when they want to go about with a golden touch.

name: Withergate Mask
description: Be the talk of any town with this fabulously spooky mask.

name: Magic Circlet (Green)
description: Impossibly thin metal, woven into a gorgeous head circlet. How do the Elves do it?

name: Magic Circlet (Orange)
description: Impossibly thin metal, woven into a gorgeous head circlet. How do the Elves do it?

name: Magic Circlet (Red)
description: Impossibly thin metal, woven into a gorgeous head circlet. How do the Elves do it?

name: Legionnaire Helmet
description: Armor based on designs of ancient Nel'Varian origin, recreated with a modern flair by Poppy. But when did the Nel'Varians need metal armor... and why?

name: Legionnaire Chest Plate
description: Armor based on designs of ancient Nel'Varian origin, recreated with a modern flair by Poppy. But when did the Nel'Varians need metal armor... and why?

name: Legionnaire Legs
description: Armor based on designs of ancient Nel'Varian origin, recreated with a modern flair by Poppy. But when did the Nel'Varians need metal armor... and why?

name: Legionnaire Gloves
description: Armor based on designs of ancient Nel'Varian origin, recreated with a modern flair by Poppy. But when did the Nel'Varians need metal armor... and why?

name: Magic Circlet (Purple)
description: Impossibly thin metal, woven into a gorgeous head circlet. How do the Elves do it?

name: Magma Gloves
description: Gloves of elemental fire, forged by ancient Elemental smiths using a technique that modern smiths have been unable to successfully replicate.

name: Money Maker Gloves
description: An enchanted pair of gloves that conjures images of vast wealth about your person. Make it rain!

name: Archeologist Gloves
description: Bronze armor crafted in the form of a fearsome dragon, crafted by the earliest Human settlers of Sun Haven.

name: Magma Headband
description: A headband of elemental fire, forged by ancient Elemental smiths using a technique that modern smiths have been unable to successfully replicate.

name: Money Maker Tophat
description: An enchanted top hat that conjures images of vast wealth about your person. Make it rain!

name: Curator Headwear
description: It is not merely the thrill of the hunt, but also the satisfaction of history preserved, wot-wot.

name: Archeologist Hat
description: Bronze armor crafted in the form of a fearsome dragon, crafted by the earliest Human settlers of Sun Haven.

name: Magma Pants
description: Legguards of elemental fire, forged by ancient Elemental smiths using a technique that modern smiths have been unable to successfully replicate.

name: Archeologist Pants
description: Bronze armor crafted in the form of a fearsome dragon, crafted by the earliest Human settlers of Sun Haven.

name: Money Maker Pants
description: An enchanted pair of pants that conjures images of vast wealth about your person. Make it rain!

name: Curator Legs
description: Durable enough for intense treasure hunting, yet posh enough for the finest of gentlemanly gatherings.

name: Magma Chestplate
description: A chestplate of elemental fire, forged by ancient Elemental smiths using a technique that modern smiths have been unable to successfully replicate.

name: Money Maker Coat
description: An enchanted coat that conjures images of vast wealth about your person. Make it rain!

name: Archeologist Chest
description: Bronze armor crafted in the form of a fearsome dragon, crafted by the earliest Human settlers of Sun Haven.

name: Curator Torso
description: Durable enough for intense treasure hunting, yet posh enough for the finest of gentlemanly gatherings.

name: Archeologist Cape
description: A garment treated with a special oil, making it water tight and resistant to pesky dust!

name: Adamant Helmet
description: A mind is a terrible thing to waste, so keep yours protected with this metal helmet.

name: Adamant Chest Plate
description: Super heavy, but is great protection.

name: Adamant Legs
description: They clank whenever you walk, but they'll keep your legs shielded.

name: Soldier's Boots
description: Made of durable leather, fitting footwear for long marches over any terrain.

name: High Jumper Shoes
description: Bouncy rubber shoes. These will really put a spring in your step!

name: Adamant Gloves
description: Keeps your fingers safe!

name: Copper Helmet
description: A mind is a terrible thing to waste, so keep yours protected with this metal helmet.

name: Copper Chest Plate
description: Super heavy, but is great protection.

name: Copper Legs
description: They clank whenever you walk, but they'll keep your legs shielded.

name: Copper Gloves
description: Keeps your fingers safe!

name: Anubis Headpiece
description: An ornate helmet, based on an ancient style of armor worn by the Amari. It's been reproduced with modern materials, making it quite durable.

name: Anubis Chest Piece
description: An ornate chest plate, based on an ancient style of armor worn by the Amari. It's been reproduced with modern materials, making it quite durable.

name: Anubis Legs
description: Ornate plate boots, based on an ancient style of armor worn by the Amari. It's been reproduced with modern materials, making it quite durable.

name: Anubis Gloves
description: Ornate plate gloves, based on an ancient style of armor worn by the Amari. It's been reproduced with modern materials, making it quite durable.

name: Iron Helmet
description: A mind is a terrible thing to waste, so keep yours protected with this metal helmet.

name: Iron Chest Plate
description: Super heavy, but is great protection.

name: Iron Legs
description: They clank whenever you walk, but they'll keep your legs shielded.

name: Iron Gloves
description: Keeps your fingers safe!

name: Mithril Helmet
description: A mind is a terrible thing to waste, so keep yours protected with this metal helmet.

name: Mithril Chest Plate
description: Super heavy, but is great protection.

name: Mithril Legs
description: They clank whenever you walk, but they'll keep your legs shielded.

name: Sunite Helmet
description: A helmet forged of Sunite, few could be finer.

name: Mithril Gloves
description: Keeps your fingers safe!

name: Aspect of the Sun
description: Adorned with a striking sunfire crest, this is the most masterfully crafted helmet you've ever seen.

name: Sunite Chest Plate
description: A chest plate forged of Sunite, you'd dare any foe to hurt you through this!

name: Sunite Legs
description: Legplates forged of Sunite, they're very heavy and offer unparalleled protection for your legs.

name: Sunite Gloves
description: Plated gloves forged of Sunite, your fingers will definitely thank you for wearing them.

name: Phantom Plate Helmet
description: A heavy plate helmet, you've never seen armor crafted like this before... where did Dynus get this?

name: Phantom Chest Plate
description: A heavy chestplate, you've never seen armor crafted like this before... where did Dynus get this?

name: Phantom Plate Legs
description: A pair of heavy plate legs, you've never seen armor crafted like this before... where did Dynus get this?

name: Phantom Plate Gloves
description: A pair of heavy plate gauntlets, you've never seen armor crafted like this before... where did Dynus get this?

name: Fancy Pants (Black)
description: Why yes, my pants ARE fancy. Thanks for noticing.

name: Love Letter
description: Gift this to an NPC to start dating them.

name: Memory Loss Potion
description: It looks less like a liquid and more like an eerie sort of fog... like a mental haze, obscuring memory and committing it to oblivion.

name: Copper Ring
description: A simple looking copper ring, it has actually been enchanted to impart increased strength to its wearer.

name: Iron Ring
description: A simple looking iron ring, it has actually been enchanted to impart increased strength to its wearer.

name: Adamant Ring
description: A simple looking adamant ring, it has actually been enchanted to impart increased strength to its wearer.

name: Mithril Ring
description: A simple looking mithril ring, it has actually been enchanted to impart increased strength to its wearer.

name: Sunite Ring
description: A resplendent ring forged of Sunite, it has been enchanted to impart increased strength to its wearer.

name: Glow Ring
description: A conjured spark has been carefully set into this ring using magic, making it a handy source of light.

name: Bonding Ring
description: A pretty heart-shaped gem that has been enchanted to increase the wearer's favor among their peers.

name: Enchanted Wedding Ring
description: A ring, enchanted by the very magic of the love you and your spouse share for one another.

name: Butterfly Ring
description: A beautiful ring enchanted with the essence of butterflies, summoning a butterfly companion who protects you from the first instance of damage taken every 30 seconds.

name: Engagement Ring
description: The perfect way to propose. Gift this to your true love when the time is right to ask them to marry you.

name: Golden Egg Ring
description: Who needs a golden goose? Enchanted with the mystical might of eggs, this golden ring grants its wearer a chance to conjure their own golden eggs.

name: Morning's Light Ring
description: Enchanted under the light of a morning sun, this ring imbues its wearer with increased vigor.

name: Shadow Ring
description: A moon insignia holds a small bead of captured shadows, imbuing its wearer with increased vigor.

name: Sapphire Ring
description: A roughly cut sapphire set in a band of iron, it trades away elegant beauty in exchange for vitality and might.

name: Ruby Ring
description: A roughly cut ruby set in a band of iron, it trades away elegant beauty in exchange for vitality and might.

name: Amethyst Ring
description: A roughly cut amethyst set in a band of iron, it trades away elegant beauty in exchange for vitality and might.

name: Havenite Ring
description: A ring of chiseled havenite, there are few like it in the world.

name: Diamond Ring
description: Throughout all the regions of the land, there's no ring quite as iconic or as classic as a diamond.

name: Farmer's Ring
description: An emerald ring bearing the crest of a rising sprout. If you can't have a green thumb, at least you can have a green ring.

name: Fisherman's Band
description: A band of iron smelted into the shape of a fish, fishermen swear it's their ultimate lucky charm.

name: Miner's Blessing Ring
description: A miner's insignia, carried by wayward miners as a token of protection while they dig through the dark earth. It increases one's affinity for mining when worn.

name: Explorer's Blessing Ring
description: A ring that has been enchanted to give extra speed and stamina to its wearer, adventurers are quite fond of its ability to hasten travels.

name: Fisherman's Blessing Ring
description: A strange ring of carved leviathan bone, a fisherman's incantation has been placed on it, increasing one's fishing prowess.

name: Bounty Hunter's Ring
description: Wearing this ring signifies its wearer as a bounty hunter- so bounties beware!

name: Ring of Quiet
description: A powerful enchantment on this ring suppresses the noise its wearer makes, this would really come in handy while fishing.

name: Lost Mage's Ring
description: A traveling mage must have dropped this enchanted ring. Oh well, finders keepers!

name: Fruit Ring
description: Tiny gemstones carved into the shape of fruit are set on this ring. Imbued with the spirit of fruit, it grants proficiency in growing crops.

name: Gold Scrap Ring
description: An enchanted ring crafted from a flake of discarded gold, it brings its wearer great luck in financial fortune.

name: Cracked Mage's Ring
description: Some power or force has cracked this enchanted ring nearly in two. The power of its enchantment is now wild and barely contained, becoming both powerful and dangerous.

name: Companion Ring (Left)
description: Your best friend can wear the other half! This ring increases HP regeneration by a small amount. This effect grows stronger with each person in your party who also wears this ring.

name: Companion Ring (Right)
description: Your best friend can wear the other half! This ring increases HP regeneration by a small amount. This effect grows stronger with each person in your party who also wears this ring.

name: Stone Ring
description: Someone took a stone, carved a hole in it and called it a ring. At any rate, an enchantment upon it grants great defense. So that's pretty neat.

name: Anne Wedding Ring
description: Don't think just because we're married that I'll give you a discount. Heh... I'm only joking. I love you.

name: Catherine Wedding Ring
description: I didn't need any magic to know this would be the happiest day of my life, hehe. I love you sweetheart.

name: Claude Wedding Ring
description: I've never felt this way before, about anything. You've changed how I see everything. I love you.

name: Darius Wedding Ring
description: They'll tell tales of our love for generations in Withergate, my dear. I'll see to it that they do. I love you.

name: Donovan Wedding Ring
description: The wedding thing was nice and all, but I'm just glad we can be together from now on. I love you.

name: Iris Wedding Ring
description: I don't know what the future holds, but I'm ready to face it with you. I love you.

name: Jun Wedding Ring
description: Marriage is a journey that merges two lives into one... And you're the one I want to walk that journey with. I love you.

name: Kitty Wedding Ring
description: Be honest, nya! Do you think I can ever make you as happy as you make me? I love you! Nya!

name: Liam Wedding Ring
description: I'm sorry if I'm crying. I'm just so happy that we can be a full family again. I love you...

name: Lucia Wedding Ring
description: Every leader needs to have someone standing beside them. I'm glad it's you. I love you.

name: Lynn Wedding Ring
description: When I came to Sun Haven, I didn't know for sure what I'd find. I'm really happy I found you. I love you.

name: Nathaniel Wedding Ring
description: Don't worry. Whatever happens, I'm always going to be here to protect you. That's a promise nothing can ever break. I love you.

name: Vaan Wedding Ring
description: It's about time we became one together, don't you agree? You were mine since the beginning anyways. I love you.

name: Wornhardt Wedding Ring
description: I didn't know if I would ever be able to be happy like this again. I love you.

name: Xyla Wedding Ring
description: It's a good thing you decided to join me. Together we'll truly be unstoppable. I love you.

name: Black Diamond Ring
description: A ring, set with a carved black diamond. An enchantment upon it brings the wearer a chance to find additional black diamonds.

name: Foraging Ring
description: Often worn by Elven rangers on missions in the deep wilds. Its wearer will have luck in foraging.

name: Hardwood Ring
description: A ring carved of polished hardwood, enchanted to grant its wearer great fortune... in hardwood.

name: Wesley Wedding Ring
description: Let this union be one that takes Nel'Vari and Sun Haven forward... not to mention you and I. I love you.

name: Kai Wedding Ring
description: Nothing could ever make me forget you, my dear. This ring will prove that. I love you.

name: Miyeon Wedding Ring
description: I always thought my life needed to be perfect - but now it finally is. I love you.

name: Shang Wedding Ring
description: A shattered blade, a curse broken - let its shards be reforged into something worthy and blessed. I love you.

name: Vivi Wedding Ring
description: You better take our bond seriously, because I'M sure gonna! I love you.

name: Lucius Wedding Ring
description: I love you to the Moon and back. Haha, get it? Moon joke. I love you.

name: Karish Wedding Ring
description: I don't know why we need a ring to prove our love, but if it's a ring it takes, then it's a ring you'll get! I love you.

name: Zaria Wedding Ring
description: I'll never be ready to lose again... But I'm ready to take a risk for you. I love you.

name: Tidewitch Robe

name: Tidewitch Pants

name: Winter Helmet

name: Scale Cape

name: Shiny Cape

name: Super Cape

name: Peace Cape

name: Torn Cape
description: It looks like one of the caterpillars got a little snacky with this cape...

name: Vampire Cape
description: It looks like something Claude would wear. Hah, isn't that funny?

name: Phantom Cape
description: A cloak woven of a strange material, it's completely weightless yet feels as tough as any armor.

description: Crush the chitin of your enemies upon your glorious spikes' - Old Iseronian piece of advice.

name: Lily Blossom Cape
description: If you're going to navigate a treacherous jungle, you may as well have a cool cape to wear.

name: Moth Wing Cape
description: As soft and silent as the wings of a moth, and it's even suitable for any climate!

name: Pop Sensation Heartthrob Tail
description: You? A devil? No...

name: Snow Day Ninja Scarf
description: Ninjas have to wear their scarves, too.

name: Starlight Wings
description: Cloudy wings, swept back by celestial winds.

description: A cape fit for a celestial champion.

name: Tis the Season Mini Wings
description: You may need some bigger wings if you plan to fly away into the winter night.

name: Wasp Chest Plate
description: A lacquered breastplate molded into the form of a Wildborn wasp Amari.

name: Dragonfly Shirt
description: The Wildborn Amari of Iseron dart with incredible speed through their jungle homes, chasing down prey in the blink of an eye.

name: Carnivorous Crop Top
description: Once endlessly fertile, an ancient calamity wounded Iseron. The rich soil turning dry and barren, Iseron's native plant Amari were forced to adapt to a 'different' type of sustenance.

name: Mantis Cloak
description: Living in an inhospitable jungle is no excuse for the mantis Amari to not dress their best... They may be Wildborn, but they're not animals.

name: Venus Fly Trap Shawl
description: Cloaked in jungle foliage, the predator waits for its unsuspecting prey.

name: Bee Chest Plate
description: A heavy carapace is required for survival in the ruthless jungle.

name: Blooming Warrior Top
description: Their battle garb seems to emulate the most deadly of the local plantlife.' - Unknown Curator's observation on Iseronian battle armor.

name: Royal Blossom Dress
description: There is an odd beauty in the simplicity of Iseron's royal dressings.

name: Lily Blossom Robe
description: Keeps the jungle razorstalk from scratching you - plus you look like a pretty flower!

name: Moth Chest Plate
description: Made of a very soft, slightly fuzzy and ever so dusty material, like a really nice sweater.

name: Celestial Dress
description: Begemmed with twinkling stars, caught in a galactic dance.

name: Celestial Matador Shirt
description: Strut with the confidence and swagger of a matador... A matador FROM SPACE!!

name: Blue Puppy Sweater Dress
description: A soft blue sweater stamped with the classic puppy paw.

name: Pink Kitty Sweater Dress
description: A soft pink sweater stamped with the classic kitty paw.

name: Kitty Mascot Robe
description: A robe that is just as fluffy as any kitty.

name: Puppy Mascot Robe
description: A robe that is just as scruffy as any puppy.

name: Puppy Bandana
description: A bandana that signals your membership in the cuddly puppy crew.

name: Kitty Bandeau
description: A sleek bandeau for that purrfect look.

name: Toy Cat Dress
description: The fluffy-wuffiest dress you've ever seen.

name: Toy Dog Vest
description: See my vest, see my vest, made to look like puppy chest.

name: Fluffy Pet Lover Coat
description: Pet hair gets everywhere, and on every piece of clothing you'll own. If you can't beat 'em, why not join 'em?

name: Pink Kitty Shirt
description: An extra floofy shirt to make you look just like a kitty.

name: Blue Puppy Shirt
description: An extra poofy shirt to make you look just like a puppy.

name: Cyberpop Armored Uniform

name: Troublemaker Jacket
description: Get dressed. We have a cybernetic overlord to overthrow.

name: Cyberpop Robo Jacket
description: Let them think you're a good little cyberstudent. When class is out and the teacher-bots go offline, it's battle time.

name: Cyberpop Flight Suit Jacket
description: Take control of the skies, courtesy of a cyberguard security jet.

name: Cyberpop Tanky Jacket

name: Cyberpop Uniform Jacket

name: Veteran Battle Star Uniform

name: e-Battler Uniform Jacket
description: An Acadamia jacket customized with armor padding. Stylish AND functional!

name: Battle Exchange Student Dress

name: Tech Academia Student Shirt
description: Techies aren't known for their skill in e-Battles, but when it comes to developing Frame-busting viruses, there are none as skilled.

name: Mermaid Dress
description: Specially tailored to fit comfortably over legs and tail alike.

name: Wetsuit Top
description: The suit gets wet so you stay dry!

name: Jellyfish Dress
description: Jellyfish have life figured out. Just jell out and go with the flow...

name: Wild Mermaid Dress
description: Wildborn Mermaid gather the bounty of the tides to craft their garb.

description: Just because it's made out of a fungus doesn't mean it lacks in style.

name: Froggy Dress

name: Mushroom Sweater

name: Mushroom Dress

name: Toy Phone Hat
description: Does your hat take long distance calls?

name: Raggedy Doll Wig
description: Yup, made with genuine yarn!

name: Messy Doll Hair Wig
description: They say if you have big hair, you must have an even bigger attitude.

name: Pumpkin Costume Hat
description: Pumpkins aren't supposed to have heads! Thankfully the brilliant pumpkin costume designers made this nifty pumpkin hat to hide your unsightly noggin.

name: Candle Costume Hat
description: We're not saying that melting a giant candle on your head is a great idea, but it certainly does make an awesome costume.

name: Ghost Costume Mask
description: The mouth of this ghostly hood is nice and wide to facilitate the loudests of BOOs.

name: Spooky Hood
description: Is that the possessed hood of a vengeful spectre? No, it's just an especially spooky costume!

name: Pumpkin Witch Hat
description: First sandwiches, and now PUMPKIN witches? When does it end?!

name: Happy Pumpkin Hat
description: A true pumpkin keeps a smile on their face no matter what happens.

name: Shocked Pumpkin Hat
description: Any pumpkin would be shocked to learn what they make pumpkin pie out of!

name: Scary Pumpkin Hat
description: Put the candy in the bag and no one gets scared.

name: Stitched Witch Hat
description: Stitched countless times, this witch's hat has been through it all - and is still ready for more.

name: Paper Mache Skeleton Hat
description: This hat has such a strange texture... Almost like some kind of paper, or maybe... papyrus?

name: Candle Witch Hat
description: An enchanted flame burns forever, lighting the way whilst you're on official witch work.

name: Stitched Top Hat
description: A tophat made out of some kind of strange purple fuzzy material. D-did it just growl at you...?

name: Wasp Grieves
description: Lacquered leggings molded into the form of a Wildborn wasp Amari.

name: Dragonfly Pants
description: The padded feet really cushion the impact of jumping branch to branch.

name: Mantis Pants
description: The Curators managed to find a few things of value on Iseron, such as the fascinating garments created and worn by the local Wildborn.

name: Venus Fly Trap Skirt
description: What's worse than a monstrous plant that's trying to take a bite out of you? One with legs!

name: Bee Grieves
description: I bee-lieve these are some bee greaves' - Unknown Curator, making a dad joke.

name: Blooming Warrior Skirt
description: Battle armor made from plant leather and reinforced with some sort of lacquer.

name: Lily Blossom Pants
description: The Curators were sure their leader, The Great Curator, would be impressed with the jungle clothing brought back from the Iseron expedition. Meh, he'd seen better.

name: Moth Grieves
description: Iseron is hot and steamy by day, but gets quite chilly in the night. The moth Wildborn are appropriately fuzzy to accommodate.

name: Carnivorous Skirt
description: Everyone loves a flower until, until your daisy grows teeth and a taste for flesh!

name: Celestial Matador Pants
description: Stylish and fancy, yet practical enough to go toe to toe with a raging beast.

name: Blue Puppy Boots
description: Pup-two-three-four...

name: Pink Kitty Boots
description: Specially designed booties for kitties, or for people who wish to BE kitties.

name: Puppy Paw Pants
description: Puppies love pants (Correction: Puppies love to pant from their mouth, they dislike wearing pants).

name: Kitty Paw Skirt
description: A breezy skirt that won't get in the way as you climb trees, chase birds and generally get up to mischief.

name: Toy Dog Shorts
description: The belt is a giant dog collar...

name: Fluffy Pet Lover Pants
description: Pet hair gets everywhere, and on every piece of clothing you'll own. If you can't beat 'em, why not join 'em?

name: Blue Puppy Pants
description: Extra poofy pants to make you look just like a puppy.

name: Pink Kitty Pants
description: Extra floofy pants to make you look just like a kitty.

name: Cyberpop Armored Pants
description: Don't get caught with your pants down. This is cybernetic war!

name: Troublemaker Pants
description: Slides extra slick across the hoods of rocket cars when making your crafty getaway.

name: Cyberpop Robo Boots
description: The cyberguard installed student tracking software in these boots - until it was disabled by the very student it was meant to track, of course.

name: Cyberpop Flight Suit Pants
description: Pressurized flight pants that keep the blood from rushing to your feet during intense aeriel maneuvers.

name: Cyberpop Tanky Pants
description: Heavy duty tanksuit pants, they're far too heavy to walk in without the command code activating their mobility engines.

name: Cyberpop Uniform Pants
description: Not the most comfortable pants, but then, comfort isn't the focus of anything in the year 3XXX

name: Veteran Battle Star Shoes
description: These old school uniform shoes came with hard plating across the feet and toes. In the past it was a fashion statement, but now they're perfect for a little underground fighting.

name: e-Battler Uniform Pants
description: Someone took the time to install anti-gravity plates in the bottoms of these shoes. Sadly, don't seem to be functioning anymore.

name: Battle Exchange Student Boots
description: Self-lacing boots. A technological marvel in more primitive times.

name: Tech Academia Student Pants
description: A little heavy as far as pants go. It's probably all the byte-drives someone left in the pockets.

name: Wetsuit Pants
description: It's like walking in the world's biggest pair of flip flops.

name: Mushroom Baggy Pants
description: Pants made with extra extra large pockets, perfect for carrying lots of mushrooms.

name: Brown Slacks
description: Snazzy slacks, worn by members of the illustrious Mushroomneers of Nel'Vari, an elite group of mushroom tenders.

name: Mushroom Slacks
description: Comfortable and slightly squishy.

name: Light Brown Slacks
description: Often worn by Nel'Varian foragers when out hunting for their favorite food: mushrooms!

name: Brown Baggy Pants
description: Though other races may snub it as boring, a nice earthy brown is a classic color for any self-respecting Elf.

name: Beach Shorts
description: Official legwear of beach bums.

name: Froggy Overall Bottoms
description: Froggy bottom jeans.

name: Skipper Pants
description: Snappy blue pants that are water and salt resistant - perfect for sailing over salt water seas!

name: Diver Bottoms
description: If you insist on diving into the briny deeps, you'd better have the right pants for the job.

name: Pop Sensation Cool Pants
description: Big and poofy, but still light and cool.

name: Pop Sensation Cute Skirt
description: The main draw of this skirt is obviously the bedazzling boots.

name: Pop Sensation Dancer Pants
description: Yes, they're terribly impractical to put on. But flawless fashion comes at a price!

name: Pop Sensation Emo Pants
description: Jet. Black.

name: Pop Sensation Heartthrob Pants
description: Pockets big enough to store plenty of broken hearts.

name: Pop Sensation Lead Skirt
description: These shoes weigh almost as much as you do!

name: Pop Sensation Performance Pants
description: You're dressing for fashion, not function.

name: Pop Sensation Serious Shoes
description: These shoes do exactly what you need them to do: They slip on your feet and they look fantastic.

name: Pop Sensation Singer Pants
description: Not the easiest pants to bust moves in... Which is what makes wearing them while busting said moves so impressive.

name: Pop Sensation Weeb Skirt
description: An idol should never be afraid to set a trend.

name: Fur Lined Boots
description: These boots were made for rocking.

name: Rocker Spiked Pants
description: Do my pants have enough belts on them? I feel like they need more belts.

name: Casual Rock Pants
description: They don't have any rips in them... Yet.

name: Rocking Spiked Boots
description: So heavy you can barely walk. They're perfect.

name: Metal Gladiator Shorts
description: Comfy mesh gym shorts. What? Not every piece of the outfit has to be extreme.

name: Spiked Leather Pants
description: It's always leather weather, baby.

name: Metal Dragon Greaves
description: Never stub your toe on the rock stage - or anywhere else, for that matter - again.

name: Sick Trench Coat Bottom
description: The coattails flap epically with each and every leap across the stage.

name: Metal Skull Greaves
description: The world will tremble at your metallic feet.

name: Matey Pants
description: They're actually quite wind resistant, which really helps when you're swinging onto an enemy vessel.

name: Pirate Pants
description: Don't forget to check the pockets for any spare doubloons.

name: Shanty Boots
description: They look tough, but they're actually quite comfortable. Plenty of toe-room!

name: Swashbuckler Bottoms
description: Jet black pantaloons paired with leather boots. Iconic swashbuckler kit.

name: Peasant Sailor Pants
description: Threadbare pants worn by down-on-their-luck buccaneers.

name: Captain Shoes
description: Freshly polished and ready to stomp across the deck. Show your crew who's the boss!

name: Cabin Boy Shorts
description: Keeps your legs nice and cool while you're scurrying back and forth across a pirate ship all day.

name: Snow Day Baggy Pants
description: Extra big pockets for holding anything you want (but mostly for holding snow).

name: Snow Day Thermal Pants
description: Made of special fabric that traps heat, keeping you nice and toasty.

name: Snow Day Long Skirt
description: Long and warm, so you can skirt the cold this snow day (and every other).

name: Snow Day Ninja Pants
description: Leave not a single footprint in the snow.

name: Snow Day Buttoned Skirt
description: Buttoned tight against the snow's biting chill.

name: Snow Day Casual Pants
description: Keep your snow day casual.

name: Snow Day Pants
description: Thick wool pants, keeps the snow away from your little leggies.

name: Shattered Spirit Shorts
description: Traversing the spirit realm uninvited is arduous, and interlopers often bear the scars of their trespass.

name: Spirit Tied Skirt
description: Vestments styled in the legendary outfit of the first fae-friend.

name: Spirit Moon Belted Skirt
description: A loose belt-skirt of woven hay, it is both traditional to the spirit moon festival - and allows one to pull off extra fancy dance moves.

name: Starlight Leader Boots
description: Gilded boots that enable the wearer to leap from star to star, like the Everbeyond's biggest game of hopscotch.

name: Starlight Emerald Boots
description: Elegant boots that seem to almost shine in the lusterious star light.

name: Starlight Amethyst Pants
description: The freezing void of the Everbeyond isn't exactly skirt-friendly weather, but fashion MATTERS, darn it.

name: Starlight Ruby Pants
description: No Crusaders leave a trail as bright and shining as the Ruby Wings.

name: Starlight Champion Pants
description: Polished to celestial shine.

name: Starlight Pink Boots
description: Woven with threads of light, somehow the process turns intangible bands of energy into a physical boots. We don't really know how it works...

name: Starlight Lapis Boots
description: Don't worry, all the burn marks from molten comet tails have been buffed out.

name: Starlight Armored Pants
description: These celestial sabatons are nearly impervious to damage, and their velcro bands make them super easy to put on.

name: Starlight Mascot Pants
description: Smells like feet and mascot pride.

name: Starlight Pants
description: These boots were made for walking (across the endless celestial heavens), and that's just what they'll do.

name: Ice Cream Leggings (Pink)
description: As cool as any ice cream.

name: Strawberry Party Shoes
description: Steppin' with my strawberries.

name: Tis the Season Overall Pants
description: You better believe there's jingle bells in the pockets.

name: Tis the Season Long Johns
description: Long and warm, perfect for beating back winter's chill.

name: Tis the Season Boots
description: They stay nice and shiny even when tromping through piles of snow.

name: Tis the Season Top Elf Pants
description: There's no such thing as dressing too fancy for the Winter Festival feast.

name: Tis the Season Wool Skirt
description: In the Eastern Region, long heavy wool outfits would be worn during the Winter Festival. They're hot and itchy, but certainly look quaint and traditional.

name: Toy Robot Boots
description: ERROR: "Feet" not covered in "Boots". Loading boot protocol...

name: Toy Soldier Pants
description: In the game of war, one must never be caught with their weapon gone or their pants down.

name: Toy Bear Pants
description: Do bears usually wear pants?

name: Pumpkin Polo Pants
description: Just because you're dressing up like a pumpkin doesn't mean you can't have a little class.

name: Skeleton Polo Pants
description: Do you know how hard it is to wear pants as a skeleton?

name: Snaccoon Tail
description: Love to sleep and eat? Hate doing literally ANYTHING else? Then it's time to suit up.

name: Snaccoon Shirt
description: Love to sleep and eat? Hate doing literally ANYTHING else? Then it's time to suit up.

name: Snaccoon Hat
description: Love to sleep and eat? Hate doing literally ANYTHING else? Then it's time to suit up.

name: Snaccoon Pants
