name: Snaccoon Gloves
description: Love to sleep and eat? Hate doing literally ANYTHING else? Then it's time to suit up.

name: Adventure Keepsake
description: A token kept by those whose hearts are set on adventure, it fills you with strength.

name: Romance Keepsake
description: A token kept by those whose hearts are set on romance, it imparts an air of charm to your words and actions.

name: Riches Keepsake
description: A token kept by those whose hearts are set on riches, it bestows you with great financial fortune.

name: Peace Keepsake
description: A token kept by those whose hearts are set on peace, it grants a boost to your farming skill as you cultivate the land.

name: Lynn's Shield
description: I'm going to live up to what this crest means, I promise.

name: Anne's Pearl Earrings
description: They're beautiful... I deserve to have them.

name: Vaan's Ruby Ring
description: Wow? Did a Human make this? They really do make the most incredible things! I'll save this, as a gift for someone really special.

name: Liam's Oven Mitts
description: I lost so much that day... but I didn't lose my sisters. Or you, my trusty oven mitts.

name: Jun's Diary
description: Someday I'm going to give you away to someone who will truly care to read you.

name: Nathaniel's Helmet
description: I don't know if there's anything in here worth protecting, but you do a good job at it, helmet.

name: Catherine's Charm
description: You're the strongest charm I've ever made... I want you to protect someone special to me.

name: Kitty's Cat Toy
description: Oh little mousey, maybe there's someone out there who will make me as happy as you do, nya!

name: Claude's House Key
description: A spare house key? What am I ever going to do with this?

name: Darius's Royal Heirloom
description: I wonder if I will ever meet someone worthy of accepting this... Not likely.

name: Xyla's Queen Chess Piece
description: A king might rule, but it takes a queen to get things done.

name: Donovan's Dog Tag
description: From now on, I'm only going to march where I feel like marching... if I feel like marching at all.

name: Lucia's Fire Orb
description: I will master this power, grandfather. I swear that I will.

name: Wornhardt's Stethoscope
description: As sure as my own heart beats, I will always be there for those who need me.

name: Iris's Enchanted Totem
description: Woodworking is so much fun... I wonder why I've felt so inspired lately.

name: Warrior's Keepsake
description: A silver keepsake, honoring a warrior well versed in combat.

name: Wesley's Woven Necklace
description: Change is difficult, but maybe it's more necessary than I thought. Hmph.

name: Time Keepsake
description: A token kept by those who value their time above all else, wielding this proves you're tired of all these homesick Lynns on this intro cutscene train.

name: Kai's Golden Necklace
description: This amulet is nothing more than a trinket from a life I've thrown away. I'm going to build a new life, in Sun Haven.

name: Miyeon's Tea Pot
description: You're the most beautiful thing I own, little tea kettle. I would love to brew tea in you, but... I'm not special enough to anyone, am I?

name: Vivi's Bone Dagger
description: I'll give this to someone worthy! Could you Imagine if I gave it to some stinkin' farmer or something like that? No way!

name: Zaria's Doubloon
description: Relying on other people made me miserable. From now on, I'm putting my faith in things that can't run away from me.

name: Lucius' Moon Beads
description: With these beads, may we and the sweet, brilliant light of the Everbeyond be just a tiny little bit closer...

name: Shang's Sealed Sword
description: What was said to be a terrible curse was actually a wonderful blessing. How could I have been so blind?

name: Karish's Trident
description: This is the most INCREDIBLE thing I own! I'll never give it away! Well, not unless it's to someone SUPER special!

name: Basic Fishing Rod
description: Basic, but perfectly functional. A great start for learning how to fish.

name: Very Good Fishing Rod
description: A high quality rod and line, it's designed for those looking to take their angling to the next level. Increases Fishing skill by 5.

name: Nel'Vari Fishing Rod
description: Masterfully crafted of fine wood, the Elves really know how to make a fishing rod. Increases Fishing skill by 12, increases spawn rate of fish in Nel'Vari by 15% and reduces slider speed during the minigame by 15%.

name: Branch Fishing Rod
description: Appears to just be a branch with some fishing line, though it's actually of very high Elven quality. Increases Fishing skill by 5 and reduces slider speed during the minigame by 15%.

name: Golden Fishing Rod
description:
Though it's only painted gold, it's enchanted to grant coins every time you catch a fish. Nice! 

Increases Fishing skill by 8 and grants gold coins each time you catch a fish.

name: Withergate Fishing Rod
description: Dramatically fancy for a mere fishing rod, Demon fishermen would never be caught using anything less. Increases Fishing skill by 12, increases spawn rate of fish in Withergate by 15% and reduces slider speed during the minigame by 15%.

name: Enchanted Fishing Rod
description: Seemingly an ordinary fishing rod, though it is enchanted to make Fishing much easier. Increases Fishing skill by 15.

name: Algae Staff
description:
Fed by the mana of the sun, algae is a bit magic in its own right. Mostly it's just slimy, though.

When selected on your toolbelt, this staff grants 8 bonus spell damage.

name: Bubble Staff
description:
Bubbles may look sweet and fun, but your enemies should beware - because bubbles POP.

When selected on your toolbelt, this staff grants 6 bonus spell damage and .2 Mana Regen per second.

name: Shell Staff
description:
The forlorn creatures on the sea floor absorb massive amounts of mana energy Their shells, as a result, make excellent magical weapons.

When selected on your toolbelt, this staff grants 16 bonus spell damage.

name: Squid Staff
description:
The squid do make powerful allies, if you're daring enough to trust a servant of the Deeps.

When selected on your toolbelt, this staff grants 11 bonus spell damage and .2 Mana Regen per second.

name: Coral Staff
description:
Just as the woodland Elves perfected woodcraft, their island-goer cousins perfected coralcraft. Unsurprisingly, it seems Brinestone does trade with the sea Elves.

When selected on your toolbelt, this staff grants 30 bonus spell damage.

name: Rusty Watering Can
description: The rust has caused a few holes to form in this can, but it will still hold some water.

name: Apple Jam
description: Sweet jam made from apples, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your farming skill.

name: Blueberry Jam
description: Sweet jam made from blueberries, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your fishing skill.

name: Raspberry Jam
description: Sweet jam made from raspberries, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your mining skill.

name: Strawberry Jam
description: Sweet jam made from strawberries, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your combat skill.

name: Orange Jam
description: Sweet jam made from oranges, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your exploration skill.

name: Peach Jam
description: Sweet jam made from peaches, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your farming and fishing skills.

name: Tomato Jam
description: A yummy tasting jam made from tomatoes. I bet in the future they'll put this on everything. Eating this will give you a boost to your combat and farming skills.

name: Banana Jam
description: Sweet jam made from bananas, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your farming and exploration skills.

name: Cinnaberry Jam
description: Spiced jam made from cinnaberries, fire crystals and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your combat and farming skills.

name: Shimmeroot Jam
description: Spiced jam made from shimmeroot, fire crystal and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your exploration skill.

name: Grape Jam
description: Sweet jam made from Elven grapes, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your mining skill.

name: Mana Gem Jam
description: Sparkling jam made from mana gems, water crystal and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your fishing skill.

name: Dragon Fruit Jam
description: Spicy jam made from dragonfruit, earth crystal and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your mining and fishing skills.

name: Tombmelon Jam
description: Tart jam made from tombmelon and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your farming skill.

name: Prickletot Pear Jam
description: Surprisingly sweet jam made from a young prickly pear and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your combat skill.

name: Pricklepop Pear Jam
description: Surprisingly sweet jam made from a mature prickly pear and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your exploration skill.

name: Soul Orb Jam
description: Faintly glowing jam made from soul orbs, plenty of sparkling dust and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a massive boost to your farming and fishing skills.

name: Golden Pomegranate Jam
description: Golden jam made from golden pomegranates and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your exploration and farming skills.

name: Mana Potion
description: A potion of distilled mana essense, it provides a quick boost to your energy.

name: Health Potion
description: A potent restoratrive tonic, it hastens recovery and mends wounds.

name: Attack Potion
description: An alchemic mixture that temporarily increases strength and attack power.

name: Speed Potion
description: A fizzing, shaking potion that threatens to wiggle right out of your hands. It temporarily increases speed and agility.

name: Defense Potion
description: A thick, syrupy potion that temporarily hardens the skin and increases defense.

name: Advanced Attack Potion
description: Imbued with the incredible strength of the dragons themselves, this potion boosts the strength of physical attacks for a short time.

name: Advanced Defense Potion
description: Imbued with the indomitable spirit of the dragons themselves, this potion boosts defense for a short time.

name: Advanced Spell Damage Potion
description: Imbued with the arcanic might of the dragons themselves, this potion boosts spell casting potency for a short time.

name: Elixir of Fortitude
description: An elixir brewed from the shed scale of a mighty fire dragon, it will increase longevity when consumed.

name: Elixir of Mind
description: An elixir made of waters drawn from an enchanted pool found only in the lost Elven village of Nel'Vari, drinking it expands the mind and increases clarity.

name: Elixir of Speed
description: An elixir made from a rare and exotic berry, drinking too many of them may have... especially fast results.

name: Elixir of Arcane Might
description: An elixir distilled from the poison of a jungle plant, this potent tonic imparts magical prowess to its drinker.

name: Elixir of Ferocity
description: The juice of a Snakethorn cactus has been fermented into this potent elixir, increasing the drinker's strength and fury.

name: Elixir of Iron Will
description: An elixir brewed from the crushed stones of a legendary mountain, a small part of the unyielding mountain is imparted onto those who drink it.

name: Tomato Juice
description: Tomatoes cooked down into a juice. For all the sugar in it, it's still pretty bitter.

name: Tomato Bread
description: A spongey loaf of soft bread, it smells deliciously seasoned and savory.

name: Kettle Chips
description: Extra thick sliced potatoes, battered in sugar and deep fried. Super unhealthy and even more super delicious.

name: French Fries
description: Finely cut potatoes fried in oil until golden, crispy and ready to be showered in salt.

name: Tentacle Kebab
description: Pieces of juicy tentacles stuck on a skewer and then dunked in oil. A Withergate carnival staple.

name: Plain Pretzel
description: Mere bread dough boiled prior to being baked... how do they turn out so brown and delicious?

name: Corn Dog
description: A hotdog that has been breaded in cornmeal, stuck on a stick and fried in oil. Food this bad shouldn't taste so good.

name: Berry Glazed Pretzel
description: A crispy pretzel fresh from the oven and glazed with a sugary berry syrup.

name: Marshmallow Ghost
description: A marshmallow cut into the shape of a ghost. Simple, yet cute and fun.

name: Salted Pretzel
description: A pretzel slathered in fresh butter and then showered with chunks of sea salt.

name: Chocolate Pretzel
description: Someone absolute madman dunked this pretzel into melted chocolate. Was the world ready for this? Maybe not, but it's still delicious.

name: Caramel Apple
description: A sour green apple dipped into a generous amount of caramel sauce. The bitter of the apple compliments the sweetness of the caramel quite well.

name: Candy Apple
description: A sweet red apple absolutely coated with a thick sugar glaze. The sugar of the glaze really brings out of the sugar of the apple.

name: Overly Iced Cupcake
description: A pile of sugary pink frosting. We promise there's a cupcake in there somewhere!

name: Banana Peel Pie
description: The peel is really just there for presentation, you're meant to remove it before eating. Although if you're feeling especially adventurous...

name: Candy Kebab
description: Pieces of candy kebabed on a candy skewer, you're not sure how anyone got the notion to make something like this, but you're not going to question it. Get chomping!

name: Devil Donut
description: A devilishly delicious pastry that's been fried in oil and frosted in heavy icing. If eating this donut is wrong, trust us, you won't wanna be right.

name: Ice Cream Sandwich
description: A dollop of ice cream squished between two chocolate wafer cookies. No, you can't eat it for lunch "because it's a sandwich".

name: Moon Cream Pie
description: A delicate and airy puff pastry topped with a whipped orange crème. It's practically begging you to indulge in one... or two. Or three. Or eight.

name: Cotton Candy
description: The culinary Demons of Withergate have developed a method of spinning heated sugar in a bowl, cooling it into sweet strings. Light as cotton, yummy as candy. Ingenious.

name: Festive Oranges
description: Special oranges picked for the lantern festival.

name: Spicy Shrimp Ramen
description: Tiny shrimp fried in extra hot pepper sauce, ramen doesn't taste meaner than this.

name: Pork Ramen
description: Rice noodles are noodles made with rice, so it's sort of like two foods in one. Sort of.

name: Egg Ramen
description: Delicate egg noodles floating in a savory broth, topped with hard boiled eggs. Eggsactly what you need for the perfect bowl of ramen.

name: Moon Cake
description: A festive and delicious cake that is best shared with friends and family to truly celebrate the lantern festival.

name: Chow Mein
description: "Chow mein" translates to "Fried noodles", which is a very fitting named, considering this dish is made primarily of fried noodles!

name: Dumplings
description: What's a lantern festival without dumplings? Let's hope we never have to find out.

name: Rice Ball Soup
description: The rice balls aren't actually made out of rice, but a dough made from rice flour. "Rice flour ball soup" just doesn't sound as nice, though.

name: Mining Essence
description: Ancient Nel'Varian mana, distilled into a consumable potion. This one contains the essence of earthen caverns and stone.

name: Fisherman's Essence
description: Ancient Nel'Varian mana, distilled into a consumable potion. This one contains the essence of rivers and streams.

name: Woodcutter's Essence
description: Ancient Nel'Varian mana, distilled into a consumable potion. This one contains the essence of deep forests and the trees.

name: Fortitude Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows fortitude when tapped.

name: Mind Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows mental stamina when tapped.

name: Arcane Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows arcanic might when tapped.

name: Defense Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows increased defenses when tapped.

name: Strength Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows great strength when tapped.

name: Rock Candy Gem
description:
This is taking the idea of "rock candy" a bit too literally...

This candy gem can be used as a potion ingredient at the alchemy table.

name: Hard Butterscotch Gem
description:
This gemstone looks just like a yummy butterscotch candy. Hopefully it tastes like it, too.

This candy gem can be used as a potion ingredient at the alchemy table.

name: Jawbreaker Gem
description:
Think normal jawbreakers are hard? Try eating one made out of solid gemstone!

This candy gem can be used as a potion ingredient at the alchemy table.

name: Small Blue Glorite Crystal
description:
Crystalized mana and power, in the form of blue glorite. It can be drained to increase your maximum mana. Elios warned you of the negative effects of consuming glorite's power... but he isn't here right now, is he?

Blue glorite is said to fuel Dynus's inexhaustible mana reserves.

description:

name: Incredible Spell Damage Potion
description:
A powerful potion brewed from the candy gems found in the monsterfolk lands.

You want my favor... yet you offer me mere candy? Monsterfolk... are so foolish. - Dynus

name: Incredible Attack Potion
description:
A powerful potion brewed from the candy gems found in the monsterfolk lands.

Such power this 'candy' possesses... perhaps the monsterfolk have something to offer me after all. - Dynus

name: Incredible Defense Potion
description:
A powerful potion brewed from the candy gems found in the monsterfolk lands.

You want my favor... yet you offer me mere candy? Monsterfolk... are so foolish. - Dynus

description: A hearty meal that will leave you satisfied for hours after.

name: Charcuterie Board
description: A board filled with various snacks, perfect for a party, or just for me.

name: Frostfin Seltzer
description: This drink will make you the talk of any party!

name: Blizzard Berry Stew
description: This stew will cool you down after just one bite. Brrrr!

name: Yam Fettuccine Alfredo
description: This pasta dish isn't actually pasta, the noodles are made with yams!

name: Lemon Jam
description: Lemony tart jam made from freshly pulped lemon. Eating this will give you a boost to your farming skill.

name: Pineapple Jam
description: Sweet citrus jam made from freshly pulped pineapple. Eating this will give you a boost to your exploration skill.

name: Guava Jam
description: A tropical jam made from freshly pulped guava. Eating this will give you a boost to your mining skill.

name: Triangle Jam
description: Even math is delicious if you put enough sugar on it. Eating this will give you a boost to your combat and fishing skills.

name: Kiwi Juice
description: With a gentle citrus undertone, this juice would go great in a fruit punch.

name: Watermelon Juice
description: New: Drinkable Watermelon.

name: Galaxy Smoothie
description: A smoothie packed with a galaxy of flavors... literally!

name: Honeybrew
description: A drink brewed from the honey tapped in the Grand Tree of Nel'Vari. Thick, rich and dangerously addictive.

name: Super Galaxy Smoothie
description: A smoothie packed with a galaxy of flavors... literally!

name: Citrus Star Fruit
description: These star fruit grow on the beaches of the Southern Isle, though they took exceptionally well to growing under water as well.

name: Nautitrine Fruit
description: An extremely delicate fruit, it feels like wobbly gelatin and withers ever so slightly when outside of the water.

name: Brine Berry
description: A bitter berry with an oddly fuzzy shell, its overpowering salty taste definitely justifies the name.

name: Trench Nut
description: A hard nut that grows native in undersea trenches, the meat inside is soft and juicy but the outside is tough and decidedly un-juicy.

name: Scallo-Papaya
description: Don't let the name fool you. It's literally just a scallop.

name: Kelp Soup
description: The broth is extra-salty, making this soup heavier than water... And barely edible.

name: Kelp Bun
description: Made with strong watery kelp instead of yucky dry wheat.

name: Algae Dipped Pretzel
description: In The Deeps, algae is known as "the sugar of the sea". You're not sure why, because it definitely doesn't TASTE anything like sugar...

name: Sea Salt Twist
description: Honestly, it's a darn good pretzel. So good, in fact, that you won't even question how they baked it under water.

name: Fish Roll
description: These fish are on a roll! A roll to your tummy!

name: Jelly Pop
description: How do you make jelly under the sea? Oh well, don't think - just eat.

name: Sand Dollar Cookie
description: Aw, how cute, it's a cookie baked like a sand dollar... Oh, wait. No. It's just a frosted sand dollar. Figures.

name: Conch Cone
description: If you hold it to your mouth, you can taste the ocean.

name: Saltwater Lollipop
description: Super sweet, though it certainly doesn't skip on the salt.

name: Saltwater Taffy
description: A true speciality of the The Deeps and easily the most popular candy found down where it's wetter.

name: Brined Coconut Water
description: Like the name implies, it's coconut water... brined to, um, perfection.

name: Briney Surprise
description: Surprise! It's heavily brined!

name: Beach Sand Mixer
description: Mixed with four different kinds of sand. Delicious...

name: Brineapple Punch
description: Far more brine than apple. Big surprise.

name: Tropical Slime
description: It's obvious what makes it slime, but what exactly makes it tropical...?

name: Sea Explorer's Potion
description: The swift winds of the Southward Sea, captured in a speed boosting elixir.

name: Briny Mage's Potion
description: It's not quite a potion so much as it is bottled sea water... but it's bursting with primordial mana.

name: Watery Protector's Potion
description: A few handfuls of crumbled leviathan husk, a few enchanting words, and you've got yourself a potent defensive potion.

name: Oceanic Hero's Potion
description: Deathspine Sea Cucumbers can take down a dragon with one tiny sting, their potent venom is distilled into this elixir to impart a warrior's ferocity.

name: Healthy Seafarer's Potion
description: A drought of different sailor's brews swashed together in an iron cask. While it tastes disgusting, it'll have you feeling healthy as a seahorse.

name: Brine Berry Salad
description: A salad as unpleasant and briney as the underwater denizens who traditionally prepare it.

name: Scallo-Papaya Fritters
description: Hey, people say it's a fruit so it must be healthy to eat, right?

name: Nautitrine Crab Kabob
description: Juicy fruit chunks paired with lightly grilled crab, light on the tummy but strong on the flavor.

name: Poached Trench Nut
description: Poaching these things is about the only way to get them out of their rock-hard shells, though the flavor is worth the labor.

name: Citrus Star Soup
description: Enjoyed by many citizens of The Deeps when they're feeling a bit (literally) green around the gills.

name: Fathom Fruit Linguine
description: Who would have fathomed pairing linguine with a fruit?

name: Citrus Star Tart
description: The firm touch of salt water actually lends itself surprisingly well to this tart's unusual taste.

name: Trench Nut Crumble
description: Topped with whipped cream - only, how do you whip cream under the sea?

name: Nautitrine Sorbet
description: Kind of like a frozen gelatin, only it's hard to eat without it floating straight out of the cone.

name: Brine Berry Sorbet
description: An incredibly exotic treat with a flavor profile like none other, it has just the right amounts of sweet and brine.

name: Scallo-Papaya Smoothie
description: You have to admit, it tastes a LOT better than you thought it would.

name: Citrus Star Juice
description: Freshly squeezed and ready to be sipped by the seaside... Or wherever you feel like sipping it, really.

name: Trench Nut Milk
description: Finally, a non-dairy milk alternative for fish people.

name: Nautitrine Juice
description: Sickly sweet and dangerously addictive.

name: Brinestone Boil
description: Brinestone Deep's official dish, not only because it utilizes many of the natural crops in the area, but also because it happens to be Boss Jabbu's favorite meal.

name: Scallo-Papaya Jam
description: Briney jam made from Scallo-papaya, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your farming skill.

name: Trench Nut Jam
description: Briney jam made from Trench Nut, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your combat skill.

name: Citrus Star Jam
description: Briney jam made from Citrus Star, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your mining skill.

name: Brine Berry Jam
description: Briney jam made from Brine Berry, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your exploration skill.

name: Nautitrine Fruit Jam
description: Briney jam made from Nautitrine, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your fishing skill.

name: Fathom Fruit Jam
description: Briney jam made from Fathom Fruit, plenty of sugar and infused with mana. Eating this will give you a boost to your fishing and exploration skills.

name: Golden Fathom Fruit Stirfry
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Golden Scallo-Papaya Risotto
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Golden Upside Down Trench Nut Cake
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Golden Citrus Star Fruit Rice Bowl
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Golden Brine Berry Pavlova
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Golden Grilled Nautitrine and Pepper Salmon
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Golden Brinestone Feast
description: A legendary dish created with golden ingredients, few mundane foods can compare to the culinary power of this resplendent meal.

name: Grilled Earlygator
description: Mmm. Tastes like chicken - not that you know what chicken tastes like.

name: Leaf Wrapped Haloopbut
description: Wrapped in a seasoned leaf and buried in smoking embers, a cooking method favored especially by Naga.

name: Leaf Wrapped Squawkmouth Bass
description: Wrapped in a seasoned leaf and buried in smoking embers, a cooking method favored especially by Naga.

name: Roasted Earlygator
description: Roast ya later, gator.

name: Grilled Bucketfish
description: The heat of the grill gives this fish the flakey, dry taste of a... grilled bucket.

name: Roasted Squawkmouth Bass
description: Tastes pretty good, considering how weird it looks.

name: Seared Haloopbut
description: Lightly oiled and seared on a hot grill, who needs a pan?

name: Seared Bucketfish
description: Lightly oiled and seared on a hot grill, who needs a pan?

name: Earlygator Roll
description: This gator is in a roll.

name: Squawkmouth Bass Roll
description: A squakin' good roll.

name: Bucketfish Sashimi
description: Raw bucket. Yummy.

name: Haloopbut Sashimi
description: A mouthful of sashimi with a name that is a mouthful to say.

name: Corn
description: A fresh ear of corn, it's not very good for eating uncooked, but it makes excellent popcorn.

name: Demon Orb
description: A perfectly round sphere of demonic energy, what could it possibly be used for?

name: Snappy Plant
description: Snips and bites at seemingly anything that comes close to it, a favored houseplant for many in Withergate.

name: Greenroot
description: Most think it's a weed, but it can be ground into a spice that livens up any dish.

name: Cinnaberry
description: Crunchy and bursting with unique spice, these berries are imperative for creating the perfect dessert.

name: Eggplant
description: The skin of this peculiar plant resembles an eggshell, but it doesn't sound hollow. What does the inside taste like?

name: Kraken Kale
description: Many monsters claim this strange crop tastes great when served with noodles. Maybe you'll just take their word for it.

name: Moonplant
description: Much like its namesake, the flower of this plant reflects light, seeming to shine just like the moon.

name: Tombmelon
description: This uncanny gourd grows naturally around tombs, making it fairly common around a place like Withergate.

name: Razorstalk
description: Though fibrous and very much leaf-like, these stalks are still sharp as razors.

name: Suckerstem
description: Resembling an average snack, the sickly sweet sap that drips from this crop can actually be quite overwhelming.

name: Soul Orb
description: A wispy sphere of pure energy, though it moves like a flame it is faintly chill to the touch.

name: Grapes
description: The unmatchable sweetness of these grapes more than makes up for the effort it takes to grow them.

name: Water Fruit
description: A soft sphere of water, the easiest way to consume this melon is to pop a straw right into it and drink away!

name: Fire Fruit
description: Flaming hot, they're hard to handle and even harder to eat, but very few fruits compare to the raging flavor of this berry.

name: Rock Fruit
description: Calling this fruit 'hard as rocks' would be an understatement. Don't chip a tooth!

name: Walk Choy
description: A crisp leaf dropped by a Walk Choy as a way of thanking you for helping it grow.

name: Indiglow
description: Though a single lily gives off only faint glow, bundles of this flower are a popular decoration, and light source, for Nel'Varian homes.

name: Mana Gem
description: Imbued with the mana of many different people, these beautiful gems glow with a soothing aura.

name: Cat Tail
description: Grassy stalks topped with a fuzzy brown 'tail' that no cat can resist the urge to pounce and paw at.

name: Honey Flower
description: Despite their name, they don't taste like honey - they just taste like  flowers. For a real honey taste, well, thats what you need the bees for.

name: Dead Crop
description: Withered and crumbling, it's as if these vines didn't get enough energy...

name: Wind Chime
description: Some Elves in Nel'Vari claim they can play this wispy sprout as a sort of musical instrument.

name: Dragon Fruit
description: Beloved by dragons and anyone else who can tolerate the spice of this fruit's fiery seeds.

name: Lavender
description: Legends say that this vibrant purple flower originally grew deep in Elven forests before adapting to the less magical soils of Sun Haven.

name: Hibiscus
description: People in the Southern Isles often wear these flowers in their hair for special occassions, a fashion choice that hasn't quite spread to the rest of the lands yet.

name: Lily
description: These beautiful flowers were brought to these lands from a far away continent. They grow very well here despite not being a native species.

name: Orchid
description: In some areas of the land an orchid represents strength and loyalty, in others it is an omen of bad luck.

name: Sunflower
description: The official flower of Sun Haven, often used to represent one's appreciation of Elios the Sun Dragon. So, sun flowers in Sun Haven for the Sun Dragon.

name: Red Rose
description: Brilliant red roses are a symbol of royalty and everlasting love, a staple in romantic bouquets.

name: Blue Rose
description: Graceful blue roses are a symbol of peace and elegance, in the Eastern Region these roses replace the red variety in wedding ceremonies.

name: Daisy
description: Wild daisies like these grow all along the countryside, though this is a domesticated species.

name: Shiiwalki Mushroom
description: A skinny mushroom stalk dropped by a Shiiwalki Mushroom as a way of thanking you for helping it grow.

name: Corn Seeds
description: Slow to grow, but each crop provides double the yield.

name: Wheat Seeds
description: Valued for its versatility and known for growing in rolling fields all across the land.

name: Lotus
description: The flowers of the lotus plant are known for representing renewal, blooming each day with a refreshed beauty.

name: Tulip
description: Tulips grow by the thousands in waving fields across the warmer parts of the Northern Region.

name: Acorn
description: Bitter when raw but sweet and nutty once baked, a famous ingredient in Nel'Varian pies.

name: Potato Seeds
description: These hearty veggies have a good chance to double their yield upon harvesting.

name: Tomato Seeds
description: Red and juicy, a common ingredient in delicious meals.

name: Demon Seeds
description: These seeds glow with a faint eerie light, growing quick and providing a fast yield.

name: Snappy Seeds
description: Mind your fingers when you harvest this hungry crop! Slow to grow, but sells for a high value.

name: Carrot Seeds
description: Orange and crunchy, a common ingredient in delicious meals.

name: Shimmeroot Seeds
description: Radiates with a faint golden shimmer, this lucrative root always produces legendary quality yields.

name: Pepper Seeds
description: Spicy, delicious, and more expensive than a typical crop. They grow so hot that they never stay watered overnight.

name: Onion Seeds
description: Savory and fragrant, a classic choice to kick any delicious meal up a notch.

name: Greenroot Seeds
description: Doesn't sell for very much, but is a popular and delicious cooking spice.

name: Cinnaberry Seeds
description: A sweet snack that can be eaten on the go or used as an important ingredient in delicious desserts.

name: Lettuce Seeds
description: Leafy and green, Lettuce absorbs moisture from the air and always stays watered overnight.

name: Rice Seeds
description: Actually a species of grass, rice is an adaptable staple for any basic cooking recipe.

name: Eggplant Seeds
description: Is it an egg? Is it a plant? It's an eggplant! Or a plantegg? Plant it and find out!

name: Kraken Kale Seeds
description: If you're not careful, this bizarre stalk will stick right to your fingers!

name: Moonplant Seeds
description: Crescent-shaped seeds that grow under the light of the moon.

name: Suckerstem Seeds
description: Sticky little seeds that some monsters enjoy munching on as a snack.

name: Tombmelon Seeds
description: Filled with sweet juice, these plants might look spooky but taste great.

name: Razorstalk Seeds
description: Looking more like thorns than seeds, it's the plant of choice within the Withergate royal gardens.

name: Soul Orb Seeds
description: A pale white seed that softly hums with a strange energy.

name: Grape Seeds
description: Cultivated by Elves around the world, this species of grape is adaptable to many different climates.

name: Water Fruit Seeds
description: Elementally imbued seeds that sprout into one of three different crops, you'll have to plant them and find out! Elemental Crops take 6 days to grow and each sells for a different base yield of 10, 16, or 20 mana orbs.

name: Fire Fruit Seeds
description: Elementally imbued seeds that sprout into one of three different crops, you'll have to plant them and find out! Elemental Crops take 6 days to grow and each sells for a different base yield of 10, 16, or 20 mana orbs.

name: Rock Fruit Seeds
description: Elementally imbued seeds that sprout into one of three different crops, you'll have to plant them and find out! Elemental Crops take 6 days to grow and each sells for a different base yield of 10, 16, or 20 mana orbs.

name: Wind Chime Seeds
description: Ethereal pitcher plants that emit a lovely chime as they shake gently in the breeze.

name: Dragon Fruit Seeds
description: Large and covered in soft green thorns, these seeds radiate a warmth you can feel even through the bag.

name: Walk Choy Seeds
description: Curious seeds that bounce about on their own accord, planting them is always a bit tricky.

name: Shiiwalki Mushroom Seeds
description: Hard spore clusters of some kind of strange mushroom, they wiggle a bit as you hold them.

name: Indiglow Seeds
description: A lily flower renowned both for its beauty and the beautiful glow it emits upon blossoming.

name: Acorn Seeds
description: Rustic nuts that are enjoyed by Elves and squirrels alike.

name: Cat Tail Seeds
description: A seed covered in soft fuzz that feel almost like fur.

name: Mana Gem Seeds
description: Tiny gems of crystalized mana, these "seeds" can only be grown by Nivara's best students.

name: Darkness Essence
description: A thick droplet of darkness energy. It feels strangely similar to mana, but... somehow twisted and wrong.

name: Darkness Essence Seeds
description: Strange seeds, they'll drop essence of darkness once their flower blooms.

name: Honey Flower Seeds
description: A strange flower bud that grows, funnily enough, in the shape of a honey dipper. Hence the name.

name: Lavender Seeds
description: Strikingly purple, even by flower standards these are intensely colorful.

name: Hibiscus Seeds
description: A flower that is popular for the sweet and tropical fragrance of its blossom.

name: Lily Seeds
description: These tend to grow the best in tropical wetlands, though they do well enough in a place like Sun Haven.

name: Orchid Seeds
description: Orchids are a customary gift when visiting old friends.

name: Sunflower Seeds
description: These flowers are famous for growing to impressive heights... they can easily end up growing taller than you!

name: Red Rose Seeds
description: Perhaps the most romantic of all the flowers.

name: Blue Rose Seeds
description: Blue roses don't occur naturally in the wild, it took years of special growing to develop roses of such a color.

name: Tulip Seeds
description: What has tulips, but no eyes or nose?

name: Lotus Seeds
description: Exotic and even a little mysterious, this variety of lotus flower actually blossoms readily on your farm.

name: Elemental Seeds
description: Elementally imbued seeds that sprout into one of three different crops, you'll have to plant them and find out!

name: Armoranth
description: This poofy flower might look soft, but its petals are as hard as iron.

name: Armoranth Seeds
description: These seeds are as hard as stone. Or, maybe more accurately, armor.

name: Balloon Fruit
description: This wild fruit actually floats into the sky as a way of distributing its seeds.

name: Daisy Seeds
description: Easy to plant and grow, daisies are popular among beginner gardeners.

name: Balloon Fruit Seeds
description: Careful, these seeds can be picked up and blown away by even the lightest breeze.

name: Barley
description: The grain of this crop is high in fiber, but more importantly, it's useful in brewing!

name: Barley Seeds
description: You can barley wait for these seeds to grow.

name: Beet
description: You have to admit, these beets can't be beat (unless a recipe calls for it).

name: Beet Seeds
description: Lumpy, irregular seeds. Are these really going to grow something?

name: Blizzard Berry
description: These berries grow best when encased under the snow of fresh blizzards.

name: Blizzard Berry Seeds
description: They're unusually sharp for seeds, which helps them grip into the soil of their icy habitat.

name: Blue Moon Fruit
description: This fruit only grows once in a blue moon, but it is worth it for a taste of the night.

name: Blue Moon Fruit Seeds
description: Even the seeds are blue!

name: Butternut
description: Better a squash than a smoosh.

name: Butternut Seeds
description: Butternut Squash seeds may look similar to pumpkin seeds, but they are actually just close cousins!

name: Brr-Nana
description: Someone cultivated a species of banana capable of growing in the frigid Northern Region. Natural banana ice cream!

name: Brr-Nana Seeds
description: Banana seeds look funny enough already, but these ones are downright crazy!

name: Candy Cane
description: The most popular winter candy.

name: Candy Cane Seeds
description: Who knew candy canes grew on trees?

name: Chocoberry
description: A standard semi-sweet chocolate on their own, but using them in recipes brings out their true sweetness.

name: Chocoberry Seeds
description: Some people like chewing on these chocolatey seeds, though they're very bitter. Worth much more when grown and used in recipes!

name: Clover
description: Do you think it's a lucky one?

name: Clover Seeds
description: Clovers don't have much value when sold, but growing them is an excellent way to gain experience.

name: Coffee Bean
description: This bean turns into a magical drink when brewed in a keg.

name: Coffee Bean Seeds
description: You must resist the urge to drink these seeds! Plant them and get even more beans to drink!

name: Cotton
description: It may be second to wool, but cotton is never forgotten.

name: Cotton Seeds
description: They might seeds, but they feel as soft and fluffy as fresh wool.

name: Durian
description: This fruit stinks! Literally!

name: Durian Seeds
description: Are you hurryin' to plant your durian?

name: Cranberry
description: Cranberries are highly valued for the sweet sauce they're cooked into for holiday feasts.

name: Cranberry Seeds
description: These seeds normally only grow in bogs, though strangely they grow just fine in Sun Haven.

name: Garlic
description: Pungent as garlic may be, it's a great addition to many dishes.

name: Garlic Seeds
description: A natural vampire repellent.

name: Fizzy Fruit
description: This curious plant naturally creates fizzy air when brewed, fizzing up any drink they're used in.

name: Fizzy Fruit Seeds
description: They say these seeds fizz and bubble when planted. I wonder why...

name: Ghost Pepper
description: If you're brave enough to try one of these ultra hot peppers just remember to drink milk and not water!

name: Ghost Pepper Seeds
description: Careful planting these, even the seeds are spicy enough to make you cry!

name: Green Beans
description: They're beans and they are most certainly green.

name: Green Bean Seeds
description: These beans will sprout into vines when planted, making even more green beans!

name: Guava Berry
description: Every part of this fruit is edible, from the seeds to the rind!

name: Guava Berry Seeds
description: Guava is a popular tropical fruit in the Southern Isles, often turned into spicy jams.

name: Heart Berry
description: A berry whose juice is often served as a drink during romantic meals.

name: Heart Berry Seeds
description: Even the seeds are shaped like little hearts, how adorable.

name: Heat Fruit
description: The fruit literal glows with heat. Watch your fingers!

name: Heat Fruit Seeds
description: Just because it's a fruit doesn't mean it can't bring the heat. A staple in the Southern Isles.

name: Hexagon Berry
description: Hexagons are nature's ultimate shape. Therefore, these are nature's ultimate berry.

name: Hexagon Berry Seeds
description: Even the seeds of this berry are shaped like hexagons. Interesting.

name: Honeysuckle
description: Flowering vines that are found native in the tundras of the Northern Region.

name: Honeysuckle Seeds
description: Weird, these seeds don't taste like honey.

name: Hops
description: Tiny little flower buds that are crucial to the brewing process.

name: Hops Seeds
description: These seeds don't seem to do much hopping.

name: Kale
description: It might not taste like much, but kale is super healthy.

name: Kale Seeds
description: Suspiciously similar to what I imagine a grass seed looks like...

name: Kiwi Berry
description: A fruit native to a specific island within the Southern Islands chain.

name: Kiwi Berry Seeds
description: Seeds of a berry grown in the warm climates of the Southern Isles. They're a little fuzzy, but in a cute way.

name: Lemon
description: Sour fruit, it can be tempered with sugar.

name: Lemon Seeds
description: When life gives you lemon seeds, grow lemons.

name: Mango
description: It's like an apple's tropical island cousin.

name: Mango Seeds
description: These seeds do best in tropical soil, but Sun Haven is southern enough in its warmer seasons.

name: Marshmallow Bean
description: Looks a bit like a bean, but tastes like a marshmallow. Name checks out.

name: Marshmallow Bean Seeds
description: Soft and pillowy little seeds, it's not hard to see where they get the name from.

name: Melon
description: Soft, ripe and perfect for a hot summer day.

name: Melon Seeds
description: They're little seeds now, but plant them and they'll grow into mighty melons.

name: Peas
description: Pass the peas, please.

name: Pea Seeds
description: Plant the peas, please.

name: Pineapple
description: Good for living in under the sea.

name: Pineapple Seeds
description: These are super tiny seeds! When you eat a pineapple you likely don't notice the seeds you're eating at the same time!

name: Pumpkin
description: Technically a fruit. A big, hard orange fruit.

name: Pumpkin Seeds
description: An important crop for any fall celebration!

name: Purple Eggplant
description: Also known as an aubergine, though it's considerably less fun to say.

name: Purple Eggplant Seeds
description: Despite the name, you're planting seeds - not eggs.

name: Pythagorean Berry
description: Forget trying to pronounce the name. Just eat the fruit!

name: Pythagorean Berry Seeds
description: Math nerds love these triangular seeds.

name: Snow Ball Crop
description: These snowballs are not for throwing!

name: Snow Ball Seeds
description: Delicate white seeds that resembles small snow balls, and just as cold too.

name: Snow Pea
description: There's no peas like snow peas.

name: Snow Pea Seeds
description: These seeds are completely frozen solid!

name: Soda Pop Crop
description: The buds of this crop fizz with air, making it the most important ingredient in the four region's hottest new drink: soda!

name: Soda Pop Crop Seeds
description: They appear to be ordinary seeds, aside from the odd popping sound they emit.

name: Star Fruit
description: Sure to be the star of whatever dish you prepare it in.

name: Star Fruit Seeds
description: Did the name the stars after the fruit, or the fruit after the stars?

name: Stormelon
description: A species of melon created by Elemental enchanters that contains the elemental force of storm.

name: Stormelon Seeds
description: Melon seeds that crackle with a strange magic.

name: Sugar Cane
description: It looks like an ordinary plant, but it's as sweet as sugar - literally!

name: Sugar Cane Seeds
description: The seeds may not be very sweet, but just wait and see what they grow into!

name: Sun Orb
description: A burning orb of energy, its warmth alone is revitalizing.

name: Sun Orb Seeds
description: Glowing with light and warm to the touch, what kind of seeds are these?

name: Tea Leaves
description: How can anyone ever be sick of tea? That’s like being sick of breathing!

name: Tea Leaf Seeds
description: Once grown only in remote lands across the Eastern Sea, tea has become a common crop across the world.

name: Turnip
description: Turn up with turnip, if you know what's good for you.

name: Turnip Seeds
description: Turn these seeds into turnip!

name: Watermelon
description: Best enjoyed by the slice.

name: Watermelon Vine Seeds
description: Water you waiting for? Plant some watermelon!

name: Yam
description: Jam out with your yam out.

name: Yam Seeds
description: A tuber, like a potato, but naturally softer and more sweet.

name: Sandstone Fish
description: Though an average size fish, its solid sandstone scales make it quite heavy.

name: Eel
description: I hope it's not the electric kind!

name: Blue Tang
description: A group of these fish is referred to as a clan.

name: Rainbow Trout
description: It may not be every hue of the rainbow, but it's still pretty colorful for a fish.

name: Angel Fish
description: Sometimes called a "doctorfish," like Wornhardt!

name: Pufferfish
description: Infamous for puffing into a spiky ball whenever threatened.

name: Gold Fish
description: Sometimes kept in glass bowls, these fish can actually grow quite large in open water.

name: Blue Gill
description: Doesn't look very blue to me!

name: Carp
description: For a fish that spends all of its time eating algae it's surprisingly tasty.

name: Red Snapper
description: This fish can live for over 100 years, and grow to nearly 50 pounds!

name: Silver Carp
description: Glitters like real silver, but its nowhere near as valuable.

name: Whitebelly Shark
description: Just when you thought it was safe to go back in the water.

name: Streamline Cod
description: Its white and flaky meat makes this fish perfect for frying.

name: Bashful Pike
description: This fish perfers to hide in rocks and reeds to avoid prying eyes, it is quite shy!

name: Redeye Piranha
description: Not too difficult a fish to catch, the real challenge is getting it off the hook without losing a finger!

name: Blunted Swordfish
description: Not the sharpest fish in the sea.

name: Catfish
description: It doesn't look anything like a cat!

name: Red Tie Guppy
description: A tiny guppy, most fishermen only catch it to use as bait.

name: Averagemouth Bass
description: Not bad, not good. Just average.

name: Royal Herring
description: All hail the royal highness of the ocean!

name: Cuddlefish
description: Looks cute enough to cuddle, though doing so is not advised.

name: Pygmy Tuna
description: It might be a big fish, but it's a small fry compared to its deep ocean cousins!

name: Ironhead Sturgeon
description: A head like iron and a body like fish.

name: Golden Carp
description: Sailors across the oceans trade stories of a vibrantly shining carp, swimming through the waves like a living piece of gold.

name: Bonemouth Bass
description: The perfect fish, if you happen to be a dog.

name: Toothy Angler
description: The ghastly light hanging on its head is the perfect tool for navigating Withergate's dark, murky waters.

name: Living Jelly
description: Pairs well with living peanut butter.

name: Zombie Fish
description: Stinks worse than most fish.

name: Deadeye Shrimp
description: Thankfully it's out of ammo!

name: Jack'o'fin
description: It's part fish, part pumpkin and all spooky.

name: Slime Leech
description: Slimy to the touch, sometimes called "the Withergate mosquito."

name: Flamefish
description: Who needs laws of physics?

name: Purrmaid
description: A wild purrmaid! Watch out for the claws!

name: Bark Fish
description: Doesn't actually bark.

name: Unicornfish
description: A fish so wonderful and majestic that unicorns were named after it.

name: Dragon Gulper
description: A fierce predatory fish, its spiny fins are almost as sharp as its knife-like teeth.

name: Robed Parrotfish
description: Polly want a lure?

name: Snobfish
description: Everything in nature is beautiful. Except the Snobfish.

name: Velveteen Betta
description: Often kept as a pet by Elven children, its velvet frills are mesmerizing to watch in motion.

name: Crystal Tetra
description: A hardy fish covered with gemstone scales that twinkle in the light.

name: Kelp Eel
description: Often reeled up and mistaken for kelp, the Kelp Eel usually gets tossed back into the water.

name: Sky Ray
description: Named for the way it glides swiftly through the water, as if flying through the sky.

name: Tin Can
description: Filled with mud and tiny bits of algae. The water is definitely not the right place to dispose of this, yuck!

name: Apple Core
description: It's a shiny, red apple. Or at least it's what's left of one.

name: Leaf Sole
description: A strange flat fish that mimics the look of a leaf, it floats on top of water waiting to snatch passing insects.

name: Fungus Fish
description: Don't let looks deceive you! This "fish" is actually a type of aquatic mushroom! Fascinating, isn't it?

name: Horsefish
description: If hay is for horses, then what is for horsefishes?

name: Frilled Betta
description: A proud betta fish with beautiful fins, this fierce fish is no stranger to an underwater duel!

name: Axolotl
description: These strange looking salamanders reach adulthood without ever undergoing metamorphosis. They're literally just a big baby!

name: Neapolitan Fish
description: It's said that this multicolored fish is fully pink right after hatching, and gains its colors as it grows.

name: Royal Koi
description: Not actually related to any royalty, though it is a very pretty looking fish.

name: Princely Frog
description: A crown prince of all things hoppy and green, its rivals at frog court shall surely toast to your catch.

name: Spiked Salmon
description: Surviving in the waters of Withergate is no easy feat, and many species have adapted special defenses for the occasion.

name: Dumbo Octopus
description: How in the world does such an adorable little octopus find itself in the spooky waters of Withergate?

name: Ghoul Fish
description: When in the water, this extra spooky fish's transparent scales renders it nearly invisible.

name: Creepfish
description: This odd fish is known for creeping through the muck to ambush its unwitting prey.

name: Water Bear
description: In the old demon tongue this creature is known as a "tardigrade", it's common name is way cuter, though.

name: Electric Eel
description: Trust us, you're a lot better off never finding out just why they call it an 'electric' eel.

name: Redfinned Pincher
description: This species of piranha has adapted to living in Withergate waters by learning one rule: Eat or be eaten.

name: Brain Jelly
description: Brain jellies are the world's smartest jellyfish. Considering other jellyfish don't have brains, though, this isn't exactly an achievement.

name: Mummy Trout
description: Remember to remove the bandages prior to cooking.

name: Kraken
description: An immature kraken. In a few thousand years, this one will totally be worth releasing on your enemies.

name: Sea Bat
description: (Un)fun fact: each of this fish's 6,790 frills are incredibly venomous!

name: Globfish
description: Globfish are great for cooking, because they don't have any bones! Just... glob.

name: Ghosthead Tuna
description: This tuna has a jelly-like transparent head, and two big eyes that act like flashlights. Perfectly adapted for where it lives, and perfectly weird to behold.

name: Goblin Shark
description: You're unsure if this shark's strange nose makes it look kind of cute, or just kind of freaky.

name: Vampire Squid
description: A blood red vampire squid, many noble families of Withergate incorporate this haunting squid into their house crests.

name: Moonfish
description: A species of sunfish, creatively named "Moonfish", because they live in Withergate. Get it?

name: Viperfish
description: Fangs, poison and a really bad attitude. Definitely not the fish to handle if you don't know what you're doing.

name: Eel-Like-Thing
description: It's... some sort of... eel... like-thing... with a face. Huh.

name: Albino Squid
description: Hushed whispers in King Minos's court trade rumors of a tentacled squid, said to be as pale and reflective as the moon itself.

name: Bitterling
description: This fish has a reputation for tasting bitter, experienced cooks know how to prepare it in ways that are quite delicious.

name: Popeye Goldfish
description: This fish's crazy eyes gives it excellent vision, making it great at spotting prey- or your hook!

name: Clown Fish
description: Tell us a joke, clown fish. ...Oh wait, fish can't talk.

name: Black Bass
description: Caught for sport in many areas of the world, many new anglers are excited to catch this fish for the first time.

name: Salmon
description: Commonly found in rivers, though this fish is no stranger to lakes, ponds, oceans, extra big puddles, etc...

name: Tiger Trout
description: This fish uses its striped coloration to stalk between underwater reeds, much as a tiger does. Hence the name.

name: Tuna
description: So-called "chicken of the sea", but where are its feathers?!

name: Ribbon Eel
description: An impossibly thin eel, its physiology confounds scholars even to this day.

name: Koi Fish
description: A fish brought to this part of the world from a far away continent, they can grow quite large when they have enough space and food.

name: Bomb Fish
description: It's like any other regular, normal fish... except it explodes!!

name: Rock Bass
description: This bass is as dense as a rock! It packed on the pounds for a long winter.

name: Northern Pike
description: The icy waters of the Northern Region aren't an easy place to get by. Migrating south for the winter is one way to find enough food for the winter.

name: Frostfin
description: An frozen fish that prefers to blend in with the winter crowd.

name: Christmas Lightfish
description: People of the Southern Isles have the oddest tradition of topping their holiday trees with this festive fish.

name: Holly Carp
description: Deck the halls with fish of holly, fa la la la...

name: Jingle Bass
description: It jingles just like a bell! It also LOOKS just like a bell...

name: Frozen Tuna
description: Not every fish deals with winter so well.

name: Scarffish
description: It looks warm and fuzzy, but it's actually wet and slimy. Sorry.

name: Heatfin
description: A beautiful flaming fish, its bright orange color sets it apart from your typical winter species.

name: Icicle Carp
description: A lazy carp that moves so slowly it can sometimes be found with icicles hanging from its fins!

name: Blazing Herring
description: This herring is a lightning fast swimmer, keeping its body running warm even in the cold of winter.

name: Coalfish
description: Tastes considerably better than its namesake, thankfully.

name: Blazeel
description: Though native to the Magma Isles, this eel can be found as far north as Sun Haven when the weather is hot enough.

name: Inferno Guppy
description: Small, but spicy!

name: Hearth Angler
description: Its lure light not only draws prey in, but also helps cook it to a delicious crisp.

name: Scorching Squid
description: A migrant squid from the distant Magma Isles, a chain of ashy islands constantly being broken and reformed by underwater volcanic activity.

name: Magma Star
description: Far past the Southern Isles lay the Magma Isles, inhospitable to any life that can't tolerate a bit of molten lava... like this little starfish!

name: Tinder Turtle
description: There's nothing tender about a sea turtle who has a molten volcano for a shell.

name: Pyrelus
description: Native to the Magma Isles, this nautilus migrates north in the summer season to search for fresh prey.

name: Flame Ray
description: A ray that looks just like a flying fireball as it glides through the waves.

name: Molten Slug
description: Researchers would love to know more about the aquatic species that live in the Magma Isles, though traveling there is nearly impossible.

name: Searback
description: Its dorsal fins are on fire - literally! Hmm, it reminds you of a fire Elemental...

name: Flower Flounder
description: Researchers claim this fish's unique body structure helps it survive in the wild. Well, if they say so...

name: Blooming Bass
description: This clever bass uses freshly bloomed water lilies to lure in its insect prey.

name: Sunfish
description: This grouper prefers to swim at the water's surface, allowing its shimmery scales to catch the light of the sun.

name: Butterflyfish
description: Did it come from a sea cocoon?

name: Raincloud Ray
description: A popular fisherman's myth is that this ray is easiest to catch during rainstorms.

name: Floral Trout
description: The pattern of this trout's scales are uncannily similar to a floral pattern, hence the name.

name: Mud Catfish
description: A fat, lazy catfish that prefers to spend its time suctioned in sand and mud, waiting for prey to pass by.

name: Neon Tetra
description: A bold tetra fish whose striking neon colors pose not as a warning to potential predators - but a challenge!

name: Seahorse
description: Looks like a little small to ride, sadly.

name: Painted Egg
description: Can we offer you an egg in these trying times?

name: Tadpole
description: Just a tad lad.

name: Coducopia
description: Hey, this would look great in a cornucopia.

name: King Salmon
description: Please unhook his royal highness, ye base and most uncouth farmer.

name: Hayfish
description: Hay is for horses. And apparently fish.

name: Acorn Anchovy
description: Perhaps the world's least favorite pizza topping.

name: Turkeyfish
description: Gobble gobble? More like glubble glubble.

name: Trick or Trout
description: You'd rather not find it in your trick or treat bag.

name: Vampire Piranha
description: So named for its dark red belly and thankfully not for any blood sucking tendencies!

name: Ghostfish
description: A harmless jellyfish that is totally invisible in the water. All the same, however, fishermen consider this spooky jelly to be a sign of bad luck.

name: Pumpkin Jelly
description: Careful, its tentacles can leave a nasty sting... though it does go great in a pie.

name: Pirate Perch
description: Though this fish looks tough and grizzled, actually they argghhh quite tasty.

name: Autumn Leaf Sole
description: This fish experiences a physical transformation in the fall season, blending in with falling leaves.

name: Squawkmouth Bass
description: Often found 'perched' on the shoulders of underwater pirates.

name: Earlygator
description: Some gators are later. This one isn't.

name: Bucketfish
description: Often found in the bottoms of waterlogged buckets. It also... tastes like bucket.

name: Haloopbut
description: This fish's body forms a loop. For some reason. Researchers... still aren't sure why.

name: Bone Gift
description: A great gift for unusual friends!

name: Apple Cider
description: Ripe apples, pressed into a pulpy juice and spiced to cidery perfection.

name: Strawberry Milk
description: Milk... from a strawberry? Nah, just strawberry flavored cow milk!

name: Blueberry Muffin
description: A perfectly baked muffin dotted with juicy little blueberries.

name: Fruit Punch
description: A tropical drink that originated in the sunny Southern Islands, it's become a staple drink at parties and celebrations.

name: Raspberry Crepes
description: A crepe is like a fancy little pancake, filled with sweet raspberries it makes an extra yummy treat.

name: Fruit Tart
description: Aptly named, this pastry has a sharp tart kick in contrast to the sweet fruit and sugary crust.

name: Linguine with Clams
description: Thick sauce and noodles served with steamed clams, a great choice for a filling seafood meal.

name: Peaches and Cream
description: Sliced peaches served in a creamed milk sauce. This is sometimes used as the filling for a pie but it's just as good on its own.

name: Tikka Masala
description: Seared vegetables in a searingly spicy sauce, it's quite delicious if you can make it past the heat.

name: California Roll
description: A type of sushi roll native to a far, far away and mythical land that is only spoken about in legends.

name: Fish Taco
description: A little different from what most people think of when it comes to "tacos", but still very delicious.

name: Creamy Mushroom Soup
description: In the past this simple soup was made due to a lack for any better ingredients. Today, however, it's an old fashioned comfort food classic.

name: Waffles
description: Light and airy on the inside, but golden and crunchy on the outside. All that's missing is a slab of butter and a bucket of syrup.

name: Nachos
description: If they're nacho chips, then who's are they? They're mine!

name: Lobster Roll
description: Seasoned lobster meat, served in a hotdog bun of all things. A bit strange, but it totally works.

name: Pad Thai
description: Stir-fried noodles and nuts, this is served as a popular street food in cities all over the four regions.

name: Lasagna
description: A classic dish from the Eastern Region, layers of sauce and noodles that make for a hearty dinner meal.

name: Potato Salad
description: A gooey mixture of potatoes and egg, it's not like any salad you've ever heard of before but it's pretty tasty.

name: Ice Cream
description: It's just milk and honey churned in ice, but it's irresistably delicious.

name: Yogurt Parfait
description: Yogurt and strawberries, layered together and topped with honeyed oats. Unbeatable when it comes to being quick, simple and delicious.

name: Omelet
description: A basic egg dish, great for breakfast. Or lunch. Or dinner. Or whenever!

name: Fish and Chips
description: Deep fried fish served with a side of chips, can you believe some people actually call them "fries"?!

name: Lobster Bisque
description: Soft chunks of delicate lobster meat, swimming in a thick and creamy soup.

name: Grilled Cheese
description: Many a beginner chef's first dish, its simplicity does not subtract from its yummyness.

name: Onion Rings
description: Onion slices, breaded and fried in oil. Vegetables don't taste better than this.

name: Sweet and Spicy Shrimp
description: Sweetness and spiciness battle each other for dominance in this shrimp dish. The winner of their duel? Your tastebuds.

name: Seafood Gumbo
description: A thin stew of assorted crustaceans, its spice and heat perfectly accent the tender seafood.

name: Poke Bowl
description: Seasoned fish served over rice, simple fare often enjoyed by sailors while out at sea.

name: Apple Sauce
description: A soft 'sauce' of mashed apples, easy to make and even easier to eat.

name: Veggie Kebab
description: Skewered veggies roasted over an open flame, the crisp taste of the fire adds a remarkably complex taste to the veggies.

name: Strawberry Shortcake
description: Some people enjoy letting the juice of the strawberry soak into the shortcake, while others try to eat it before that can happen.

name: Mochi Covered Strawberry
description: A strawberry, covered in a thin layer of flavored mochi. A lightweight but lovely dessert.

name: Acai Bowl
description: Sweet yogurt topped with an assortment of berries, a common breakfast food for many across the land.

name: Citrus Salad
description: Fragrant and slightly tangy, it's very invigorating for only being a 'mere' salad.

name: Fruit Snacks
description: Squishly little fruit snacks, an even more fun way to eat your fruits.

name: Tuna Nigiri
description: Raw fish can taste good? Who would have thought.

name: Tortilla Chips
description: A corn tortilla, cut up and turned into delicious crunchy chips thanks to the magic of deep frying.

name: Salsa
description: A loose sauce of tomato and spices, its zesty zing certainly dresses up all sorts of dishes.

name: Mushroom Risotto
description: Labor intensive to prepare, but the savory mushroom mixed with the twice-cooked rice is an excellent reward for the effort.

name: Mochi
description: Sweetened rice paste, shaped into a spongey cake and steamed before baking.

name: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: Roast mushrooms, drenched in a thick and savory broth. A peasant meal, but still fit for a king.

name: Veggie Wrap
description: Diced veggies wrapped in a corn tortilla, the soft wrap contrasts well against the crunchy vegetables inside.

name: Trail Mix
description: A mix of energy-boosting food to keep one fueled over long adventures.

name: Churros
description: Dough sticks, fried in oil and breaded with sugar. Simple, yet very delicious.

name: Tortilla
description: A corn tortilla made of corn flour dough and baked over an open fire, it's like bread only... super flat.

name: Corn Flour
description: Made of finely milled corn. It's heavier than wheat flour and slightly sweeter, too.

name: Hydrangea Cupcake
description: A cupcake topped with an intricately piped frosting design, world famous pastry chef Ramiro is credited for inventing this style of frosting.

name: Chicken Bastilla
description: Shredded chicken wrapped in layers of paper-thin dough. This delicious pastry was the signature dish of Raine, a world-famous chef and culinary visionary.

name: Sombasu's Fortune #1
description:
A great opportunity for love will present itself to you, but it will rely on you grabbing it...

...Your lucky numbers are 9, 37, 78...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #2
description:
You will befriend many animals to fill your stables, but beware... of the clean-up...

...Your lucky numbers are 4, 33,17...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #3
description:
A sizable fortune is waiting to be delivered to you, but the sender doesn't have a stamp to mail it...

...Your lucky numbers are 66, 23, 1...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #4
description:
Somewhere out there, a Snaccoon is waiting for you to feed it...

...Your lucky numbers are 83, 21, 67...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #5
description:
Come next dawn, you shall feel compelled to water any crops you are growing...

...Your lucky numbers are 17, 41, 36...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #6
description:
You will be blessed with immense fame and adoration from all stretches of the world... on the next sunny day in Withergate...

...Your lucky numbers are 12, 25, 14...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #7
description:
You will suddenly become horrifyingly aware that you have not bathed since arriving in Sun Haven...

...Your lucky numbers are 8, 3, 13...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #8
description:
You will feel compelled to sleep tonight by exactly midnight...

...Your lucky numbers are 2, 77, 32...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #9
description:
I see... farming... somewhere in your future...

...Your lucky numbers are 14, 37, 4...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #10
description:
You will own many outfits... but never change your underwear...

...Your lucky numbers are 7, 13, 18...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #11
description:
The spirits tell me... Sun Haven's General Store shall open for business at precisely 8 a.m. tomorrow...

...Your lucky numbers are 11, 24, 55...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #12
description:
The next time you cut down a tree, you shall find logs...

...Your lucky numbers are 16, 33, 56...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #13
description:
I hear two spirits... one tells me the next time you go fishing, you shall catch nothing. The other tells me that the next time you go fishing, you shall indeed catch a fish...

...The spirits won't come to an agreeance... that's just how it is sometimes...

...Your lucky numbers are 74, 5, 23...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #14
description:
When next you place items in your Shipping Portal, you shall receive a bounty of coins...

...Your lucky numbers are 25, 74, 38...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #15
description:
I see... in the distant future... the one called "Emmett"... still... in debt...

...Your lucky numbers are 63, 37, 19...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #16
description:
You will wonder what your lucky numbers mean...

...Your lucky numbers are 4, 21, 48...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #17
description:
I see you, walking on the beach... your feet get covered in sand. It is coarse and rough, irritating... and gets everywhere...

...Your lucky numbers are 16, 9, 71...

name: Wood Plank
description: I can craft lots of things with this!

name: Fabric
description: Not as soft as silk, but very durable.

name: Hardwood
description: A log of hewn Hardwood, far more durable than ordinary wood. It's just waiting to be turned into planks.

name: Hardwood Plank
description: A plank of Hardwood, true to its name these planks are heavy! Used in advanced crafting recipes.

name: Hardwood Beam
description: A solid beam of Hardwood, usable in crafting. Beam me up!

name: Wood Beam
description: A solid beam of wood, usable in crafting. Beam me up!

name: Dead Log
description: The zombified log of a haunted tree, ready to be turned into planks.

name: Dead Hardwood
description: The zombified log of a haunted hardwood tree, ready to be turned into planks.

name: Dead Plank
description: Night of the living plank? Nah, just a deadwood plank. Used in Withergate crafting.

name: Dead Hardwood Plank
description: Night of the living plank? Nah, just a heavy deadwood plank. Used in Withergate crafting.

name: Dead Stone
description: A dark rock from the haunted forests of Withergate. You're not sure why, but something about it feels... wrong.

name: Dead Heavystone
description: An extra hard dark rock from the haunted forests of Withergate. You're not sure why, but something about it feels... wrong.

name: Elven Log
description: A log of Elven wood, shimmering with mana and ready to be turned into planks.

name: Elven Hardwood
description: A log of Elven hardwood, shimmering with mana and ready to be turned into planks.

name: Elven Plank
description: Enchanted wood, now in convenient plank form. Used in Nel'Varian crafting.

name: Elven Hardwood Plank
description: Enchanted Hardwood, now in convenient plank form. Used in advanced Nel'Varian crafting.

name: Elven Stone
description: A rock mined from the Nel'Vari mines. Like everything else in Nel'Vari, it feels slightly magical.

name: Elven Heavystone
description: An extra hard rock mined from the Nel'Vari mines. Like everything else in Nel'Vari, it feels slightly magical.

name: Refined Plastic
description: Perhaps Demonkind's most pivotal invention, 'soft metal' - easy to shape, and lasts a very, very long time.

name: Refined Glass
description: Do you have any idea how much glass this city is going to need? - Xyla

name: Refined Metal
description: A bunch of scrap metals melted down and turned into an alloy. It's messy, but it works.

name: Refined Concrete
description: A key Demon invention, who needs to chisle bricks from mountains when you can simply make your own?

name: Tin Foil
description: Makes good hats.

name: Crystal Cluster
description: A small cluster of crystals, they look freshly formed and brimming with mana.

name: Driftwood
description: Slightly waterlogged from its time adrift, it will still make some fine planks.

name: Starfish
description: Neither a fish nor a star, but still pretty neat looking.

name: Iron Bar
description: A bar of refined iron. Harder than copper, it will make excellent equipment.

name: Copper Bar
description: A bar of refined copper. Not the strongest metal, but it does the trick.

name: Ocean Treasure Chest
description: A sunken chest of long lost booty!

name: Coins
description: Known for making the world go 'round.

name: Fallen Log
description: Nature did the chopping for you. How convenient.

name: Sandstone Ore
description: A dusty chunk of sandstone, you wouldn't want to drop this on your toes.

name: Heavystone
description: A lump of extra hard rock, useful in advanced stonework.

name: Unrefined Plastic
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Unrefined Glass
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Health
description: An orb of pure energy, a valuable resource.

name: Mana Orbs
description: An orb of pure energy, a valuable resource.

name: Tickets
description: A strange looking ticket.

name: Farming EXP
description: Experience in the Farming skill.

name: Exploration EXP
description: Experience in the Exploration skill.

name: Mining EXP

description: Experience in the Fishing  skill.

name: Bonus Health
description: A permanent increase to maximum health, you'll be sturdier and take more damage before fainting!

name: Bonus Attack Damage
description: A permanent increase to attack damage.

name: Bonus Spell Damage
description: A permanent increase to spell damage.

name: Bonus Movement Speed
description: A permanent increase to movement speed.

description: Income earned by completing quests.

description: Any epic fish
