name: Golden Fathom Fruit
description: A golden Fathom Fruit! Who says there don't be gold under them waves, arrr?

name: Golden Nautitrine Fruit
description: A golden nautitrine! Who says there don't be gold under them waves, arrr?

name: Golden Citrus Star Fruit
description: A golden citrus star! Who says there don't be gold under them waves, arrr?

name: Golden Scallo-Papaya
description: A golden scallo-papaya! Who says there don't be gold under them waves, arrr?

name: Golden Brine Berry
description: A golden brine berry! Who says there don't be gold under them waves, arrr?

name: Golden Trench Nut
description: A golden trench nut! Who says there don't be gold under them waves, arrr?

name: Coral Chunk
description: It's a chunk of coral, but it's as hard as rock.

name: Shell Piece
description: They call it a shell, but it feels more like solid stone.

name: Coral Piece
description: It's just a piece of coral, but it's as hard as rock.

name: Havenite
description: A mysterious and beautiful gem, found only in the earth beneath Sun Haven.

name: Black Diamond
description: A rare black diamond. They're not found very often and are considered a miner's blessing.

name: Mithril Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Sunite Ore
description: Legendary Sunite, I should try smithing this into a bar.

name: Glorite Ore
description: A gently pulsating crystal of Glorite ore, it seems to neither reflect nor absorb any light. What could you possibly do with this?

name: Elven Steel Ore
description:
A rare form of iron ore found only in the land of Nel'Vari. Due to a ban on fire crystals, no one in the forest city is sure how to smelt it into bars.

In ancient Nel'Varian the word "steel" roughly translates to "hard as dragon".

name: Tough Dragon Scale
description: The thick scale of a baby dragon, shed and left behind. It's said that dragon scales can be used in alchemy.

name: Sparkling Dragon Scale
description: The shimmering scale of a baby dragon, shed and left behind. It's said that dragon scales can be used in alchemy.

name: Sharp Dragon Scale
description: The jagged scale of a baby dragon, shed and left behind. It's said that dragon scales can be used in alchemy.

name: Enhanced Copper Bar
description: A copper bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Iron Bar
description: An iron bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Adamant Bar
description: An adamant bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Mithril Bar
description: A mithril bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Sunite Bar
description: A sunite bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Glorite Bar
description: A glorite bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enchanted Copper Bar
description: A copper bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Iron Bar
description: An iron bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Adamant Bar
description: An adamant bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Mithril Bar
description: A mithril bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Sunite Bar
description: A sunite bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Glorite Bar
description: A glorite bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Adamant Bar
description: A bar of refined adamant, it's even stronger than iron.

name: Mithril Bar
description: A bar of refined mithril, though beautiful to the eyes its strength and durability are almost unmatched.

name: Sunite Bar
description: A bar of refined sunite, this will produce equipment of legendary quality.

name: Gold Bar
description: A solid gold bar, literally worth its weight in gold!

name: Glorite Bar
description: A bar of Glorite, ready to be turned into something legendary.

name: Elven Steel Bar
description:
Peerless and naturally enchanted steel, it shimmers in the light like a mirror.

"The Nel'Varians lost the technique of forging ore into steel, but why did they learn it in the first place?"

name: Rusty Key
description: An old rusty key, it looks like it opens gates in the mines.

name: Copper Key
description: A copper key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Iron Key
description: An iron key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Adamant Key
description: An adamant key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Mithril Key
description: A mithril key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Sunite Key
description: A sunite key crafted especially for the gates in the mines, this will lead to the mine's deepest and most dangerous levels.

name: Glorite Key
description: Constructed of Glorite, this key can open the ancient locks of King Minos's Glorite mine.

name: King's Lost Mine Key
description: An ancient key that was held by King Aster, though it became lost after his time. What was Dynus doing with it?

name: King Minos's Emblem
description: An emblem stamped with the seal of King Minos, it grants its bearer access to the Midnight Isle.

name: Wind Orb
description: "I must admit, Nivara was right... I had the potential to master this magic all along." - Vaan

name: Bushie's Branch
description: The remnants of a fallen foe.

name: Antler
description: If you look closely, you can see this antler is actually covered in very tiny scales.

name: Torn Page
description: The remains of an ancient book, unreadable runes are scrawled across the pages.

name: Spectre Slime
description: Gooey slime left behind from a spectre that has been laid (back) to rest.

name: Fur Tuft
description: A tuft of dirty fur, it's covered in mineshaft dust.

name: Dragonfly
description: Doesn't look like any dragon you've ever seen!

name: Drill Bit
description: An impressive appendage, perfectly adapted to life underground.

name: Green Pepper Flakes
description: Dried peppers, crushed into flakes. The drying process made these peppers extra spicy!

name: Ice Cube
description: A terribly cold cube of ice, it doesn't melt even on the hottest day.

name: Orange Pepper Flakes
description: Dried peppers, crushed into flakes. The drying process made these peppers extra spicy!

name: Soot
description: Smoldering ash, it's still rather hot to the touch.

name: Sticky Sap
description: Some people use this ultra-sticky sap as a glue, owing to the fact it sticks almost anything together fairly permanently.

name: Snow Ball
description: Packed so extremely tight that it feels more like a rock than snow.

name: Lava Honey
description: Sweet like delicious honey... and hot like molten lava...

name: Dandelion
description: Grown by the monster Weedil. Despite its appearance this 'flower' is, in fact, a weed.

name: Lynn's Pickaxe
description: Lynn's trusty pickaxe. Looks like Solon has taken good care of it.

name: Fly
description: Flies are pretty gross, but it's said that frogs will gift them to those who are worthy. Worthy of what, though?

name: Sludge
description: A handful of gross sewer muck, it seems some lingering magical force had inadvertently enchanted it into a rampaging monster.

name: Cardboard Box Piece
description: A piece of cardboard. With enough of these, maybe you could create something incredible?

name: Bent Traffic Cone
description: A discarded traffic cone from the streets above, looks like a crab was using it as a makeshift wizard's hat.

name: Tough Tin Can
description: Monster trash from the streets above, it seems as if the citizens of Withergate aren't ones for recycling.

name: Tough Trash Bag
description: An empty trash bag from the streets above, it's extra tough and not a bad home for a crab.

name: Croc Scale
description: Long ago the untamed swamps of Withergate were home to vicious crocodiles. Though the Demons have since made their city on the land, the crocs have adapted to sewer life fairly well.

name: Tentacrush Ink
description: A patch of gooey, congealed ink that deeply stains anything it touches.

name: Keelhaul Fin
description: Spines as sharp as needles and fins as sharp as knives... Yikes!

name: Mangler Bulb
description: A dimly glowing bulb, powered by the natural magic of bioluminescence.

name: Petrified Log
description:
A log of strange, stoney wood. Scholars would love to study this.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Phoenix Feather
description:
A wispy feather of a mystical pheonix, sometimes known as 'dragon birds'.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Fairy Wings
description:
Fairies are thought to be related to the Elves. Beings of pure mana, their wings are left behind whenever they disperse into energy.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Griffon Egg
description:
A fossilized griffon egg. This proves that griffons have lived in this area for a very long time.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Mana Sap
description:
Tree sap, dense with mana energy. Very much worth studying.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Pumice Stone
description:
Pumice is left behind by volcanic activity. Where in these lands are there volcanos?!

It would look good in a museum!

name: Mysterious Antler
description:
A strange antler. It looks quite old, and it doesn't look like it came from any sort of deer or hornsnake.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Dragon Fang
description:
The fang of an immature dragon, likely intentionally shed from the mouth to make way for big boy dragon teeth.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Monster Candy
description:
A piece of Monsterfolk candy, some scholars believe the Monsterfolk race trade candy as a form of currency.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Unicorn Hair Tuft
description:
Roughly 1% of a unicorn. It must have been lost as the magical beast galloped through the woods.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Handmade Bobber
description:
A well used fishing bobber, hand crafted in the ancient style of the Southern Isles fishermen.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Magic Staff
description:
Lost for unknown ages, this staff still radiates the faintest signature of magic energy.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Bronze Dragon Relic
description:
It's a bronze dragon, countless years have worn away its features but you'd wager it looks a bit like Elios...

It would look good in a museum!

name: Old Sword Hilt
description:
An old sword hilt, the crossguard bears an unknown crest.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Nel'Varian Runestone
description:
A stone carved with delicate Nel'Varian runes. It repels your touch ever so slightly.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Elven Headdress
description:
Despite its age, the headdress has preserved nicely. Maybe it was meant for some sort of old Elven celebration?

It would look good in a museum!

name: Old Mayoral Painting
description:
It's a portrait of an old well dressed gentleman. On the breast of his coat is the Sun Haven emblem... was this a past town leader?

It would look good in a museum!

name: Tentacle Monster Emblem
description:
This emblem is carved of a strange stone, depicting a bizarre alien beast. The words 'Cw'thlza, xx'frer'tiz O'aj'loza!' are carved into the emblem's backside.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Angel Quill
description:
A writing quill, it appears to be of Angelic origin. It has to be eons old, yet the ink on its tip is still wet.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Naga Crook
description:
A serpentine shepherd crook. If you had to hazard a guess, you would say it looks Naga in origin.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Amari Totem
description:
An old totem seemingly dedicated to the ferocity of nature. Could it be Amari in origin?

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Sun Haven Sword
description:
A chipped sword, bearing the colors of Elios. It's quite old, and seems to be ceremonial rather than for combat use.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Nel'Varian Sword
description:
A metal blade, clearly Nel'Varian in origin. It's very old, and it looks like it's seen use in combat...

It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Withergate Sword
description:
A wicked Demon blade, left to rust and degrade in the dirt. It seems old, and has clearly seen much use in war.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Leafie Trinket
description:
A monster trinket, dropped as a trophy to commemorate victory.

It would look good in a museum!

name: Tier 2 Barn Upgrade
description: Make your barn bigger! A bigger barn allows you to own more farm animals.

name: Tier 3 Barn Upgrade
description: Make your barn bigger! A bigger barn allows you to own more farm animals.

name: Elven Barn Tier 2 Upgrade
description: Use this to make your barn bigger and add 8 more animal capacity!

name: Elven Barn Tier 3 Upgrade
description: Use this to make your barn even bigger and add 8 more animal capacity!

name: Tier 2 House Upgrade
description:
Use this to make your house bigger!
<color=#6B7DA1>(Left click on a house to use)</color>

name: Tier 3 House Upgrade
description:
Use this to make your house even bigger!
<color=#6B7DA1>(Left click on a house to use)</color>

name: Tier 2 House Permit
description: Requirement to craft a tier 2 house upgrade kit at a crafting table. Sold by Emmett at the Town Hall.

name: Tier 3 House Permit
description: Requirement to craft a tier 3 house upgrade kit at a crafting table. Sold by Emmett at the Town Hall.

name: Barn Permit
description: Required to craft a barn at the Construction Table. Barns are a great place to keep farm animals!

name: Tier 2 Barn Permit
description: Required to craft a tier 2 barn upgrade kit at the Construction Table.

name: Tier 3 Barn Permit
description: Required to craft a tier 3 barn upgrade kit at the Construction Table.

name: Elven Barn Permit
description: Required to craft an elven barn at the Elven Crafting Table. Barns are a great place to keep farm animals!

name: Tier 2 Elven Barn Permit
description: Required to craft a tier 2 elven barn upgrade kit at the Elven Crafting Table.

name: Tier 3 Elven Barn Permit
description: Required to craft a tier 3 elven barn upgrade kit at the Elven Crafting Table.

name: Demolition Kit
description: Don't like where you built your house or barn? Just move it somewhere else!

name: Mailbox Demolition Kit
description: Don't like where you built your mailbox? Just move it somewhere else!

name: Spring Bridge Decor
description: A bridge crafted with a springtime flair for your farm.

name: Spring Bridge
description: A bridge crafted with a springtime flair for your farm.

name: Fishing Permit Tier 1
description: An official piece of paper permitting you to deploy extra fishing nets. Increases fishing net capacity by 2.

name: Fishing Permit Tier 2
description: An official piece of paper permitting you to deploy extra fishing nets. Increases fishing net capacity by 4.

name: Fishing Permit Tier 3
description: An official piece of paper permitting you to deploy extra fishing nets. Increases fishing net capacity by 6.

name: Land Permit Tier 1
description: An official piece of paper permitting you to deploy a high number of crops. Increase crop capacity by 10. Only one tier 1 land permit can be used per world.

name: Land Permit Tier 2
description: An official piece of paper permitting you to deploy a high number of crops. Increase crop capacity by 15. Only one tier 2 land permit can be used per world.

name: Land Permit Tier 3
description: An official piece of paper permitting you to deploy a high number of crops. Increase crop capacity by 25. Only one tier 3 land permit can be used per world.

name: Red Carnival Ticket
description: A shiny ticket won at the Withergate carnival! You can exchange these for prizes.

name: Community Token
description: A token proving your contribution to Sun Haven's community. Bernard will trade these for all sorts of amazing things at Town Hall.

name: Mana Shard
description:
A shard of twinkling mana, shed by the Great Tree of Nel'Vari. The members of the Restoration Society would be very interested in this.

"There's memory in mana, the energy that fuels all life." - Nivara

name: Candy Corn Pieces
description: Used as a currency by monsterfolk, accepted at the shops in the Withergate subway. Do you think they grow it on candy farms?

name: Kingly Ticket
description:
A ticket permitting one ride on the Withergate subway train. This kingly ticket is more likely to take you to a large neighborhood.

"We'll just charge a TICKET for the subway! Tickets are the solution to everything! Bwhaha!" - Xyla

name: First Class Ticket
description:
A ticket permitting one ride on the Withergate subway train. This first class ticket is more likely to take you to a medium or large neighborhood.

"We'll just charge a TICKET for the subway! Tickets are the solution to everything! Bwhaha!" - Xyla

name: Economy Ticket
description:
A ticket permitting one ride on the Withergate subway train. This economy ticket is more likely to take you to a small or medium neighborhood.

"We'll just charge a TICKET for the subway! Tickets are the solution to everything! Bwhaha!" - Xyla

name: Spring Token
description: A token of the spring season, these can be traded for wonderful seasonal rewards.

name: Summer Token
description: A token of the summer season, these can be traded for wonderful seasonal rewards.

name: Winter Token
description: A token of the winter season, these can be traded for wonderful seasonal rewards.

name: Fall Token
description: A token of the fall season, these can be traded for wonderful seasonal rewards.

name: Sewer Barn Access Key
description: It's a Key for an empty construction inside the Withergate sewer system.

name: Tier 2 Sewer Barn Permit
description: It's a permit for building tier 2 constructions inside the Withergate sewer system, but it reads more like a liability waiver. Sold by the Withergate Barn Merchant.

name: Tier 3 Sewer Barn Permit
description: It's a permit for building tier 3 constructions inside the Withergate sewer system, but it reads more like a liability waiver. Sold by the Withergate Barn Merchant.

name: Crafting Workshop
description: A tidy crafting area is a happy crafting area - this workshop will help you keep everything in one place! Workshops are HUGE on the inside!

name: Nel'vari Workshop
description: Elves don't normally tinker with the unknown or the unfamiliar, but when they do, they do it in forest style.

name: Withergate Workshop
description: Withergate's technological progress is unmatached anywhere else in the Four Regions. For in Withergate, there is only one rule when it comes to new inventions: Bigger and badder is always better.

name: Combat Totem
description: An enchanted totem that provides some benefits for your farm!

name: Construction Table
description: A heavy duty construction table with all the tools needed for building houses and barns.

name: Tile Maker
description: A table for cutting and shaping materials into floor tiles for your farm.

name: Painter's Easel
description:
Perfect for painting artwork to decorate your home with.

More expensive than buying artwork in a store, but the convenience is nice.

name: Basic Furniture Table
description:
A specialized carpentry bench, you can make furniture and decorations with this.

More expensive than buying furniture in a store, but the convenience is nice.

name: Advanced Furniture Table
description:
A specialized carpentry bench, you can make furniture and decorations with this. This table contains advanced recipes for experienced crafters.

More expensive than buying furniture in a store, but the convenience is nice.

name: Composter
description: A farming essential, composters turn resources into compost and fertilizer.

name: Seed Maker
description: A specialized extractor that can produce extra seeds from Sun Haven crops fed into it, multiplying your profits and letting you live off your own hard work!

name: Ice Cream Cart
description: Kept freezing cold thanks to a specialized form of water magic, you can freeze ingredients into icy treats with this.

name: Oven
description: More advanced than a basic cooking pot, turning the crops you grow into delicious cakes and desserts.

name: Sushi Table
description: A table specially designed for preparing sushi, a popular and exotic form of seafood from across the eastern sea.

name: Juicer
description: Squeeze fruit (or anything else you dare) into fresh juices. Juices provide restorative properties.

name: Mana Composter
description: Even the compost bins in Nel'Vari are beautiful! Composts Nel'Vari resources into fertilizer. Infuse dirt with mana, reinvigorating it into super soil for your Nel'Vari crops.

name: Elven Furniture Table
description: A furniture table fully equipped with specialized tools to create furniture in the fine style of the Elves of Nel'Vari

name: Mana Anvil
description:
Essential for hammering Nel'Vari metals into useful tools.

Nel'Varians never wished to make tools of war. When there was no more use for the craft, many in Nel'Vari forgot about it.

name: Mana Infuser Table
description: An enchanting table designed to aid in the process of mana infusion. You can create magic potions at this workstation.

name: Tea Kettle
description: Never settle for an inferior tea kettle.

name: Elven Loom
description: None are better at a loom than Elves, the Nel'Varians especially so. Turns Nel'Vari silk into all sorts of useful things.

name: Elven Seed Maker
description: A specialized extractor that can produce extra seeds from Nel'Vari crops fed into it.

name: Elven Furnace
description:
A metal furnace that glows hot enough to metal down Nel'Vari ores into usable material.

"An old method from a different era, yes. But one worth preserving, I think." - Gorwin

name: Fall Scarecrow
description: A simple scarecrow to frighten off fall pests that seek to steal your crops.

name: Recycling Machine
description: Even Monsterfolk recycle! This machine can recycle Withergate forageables into useful materials.

name: Monster Composter
description: An ordinary composter box... with a monster of an appetite! Composts Withergate resources into compost.

name: Monster Furniture Table
description: A furniture table fully equipped with specialized tools to create furniture in the style of the Demons and Monsterfolk of Withergate.

name: Monster Anvil
description:
Essential for hammering Withergate metals into useful things.

The Monsterfolk may seem brutish and uncivilized, but they have developed advanced crafting techniques of their own.

name: Monster Sushi Table
description:
A monster table with all the special tools needed to prepare sushi.

"The monsterfolk LOVE sushi... but where in the world did they learn to make it?!" - Phoebe

name: Soda Machine
description: A spectacle of Demonic engineering, this machine is full of drinks that automatically dispense when you want them!

name: Monster Loom
description: Monsters are great at looming, especially in creepy forests or old castles! This monster loom will turn Withergate silk into all sorts of useful things.

name: Monster Seed Maker
description: A specialized extractor that can produce extra seeds from Withergate crops fed into it.

name: Monster Furnace
description: A heavy metal furnace that glows hot enough to metal down Withergate ores into usable material.

name: Summer Scarecrow
description: A scarecrow to frighten off summer pests that seek to steal your crops.

name: Winter Scarecrow
description: A simple scarecrow to frighten off winter pests that seek to steal your crops.

name: Fishing Totem
description: An enchanted totem that provides some benefits for your farm!

name: Mining Totem
description: An enchanted totem that provides some benefits for your farm!

name: Farming Totem
description: An enchanted totem that provides some benefits for your farm!

name: Fall Totem
description: A seasonal totem to ward off rootweeds that entangle your crops.

name: Spring Totem
description: A seasonal totem that provides some benefits for your farm!

name: Summer Totem
description: A seasonal totem that protects nearby crops from being burnt.

name: Winter Totem
description: A seasonal totem that protects nearby crops from being frozen.

name: Seltzer Keg
description:
A sealed keg, necessary for brewing bunches of bombastic beverages.
"Humans, Elves, Amari... yup, seems like every race invented their own brews." - Ronald

name: Sun Haven Totem
description: An enchanted totem imbued with Sun Haven mana, it enriches the soil and allows Sun Haven crops to grow in Withergate or Nel'Vari.

name: Crop Totem
description: An enchanted totem that provides some benefits for your farm!

name: Small Aquarium
description: A silly little home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Golden Tree Seeds
description: A seed of pure gold. If planted, it will grow a golden tree. The golden tree, of course, will produce many golden items.

name: Gem Trophy
description: A golden trophy, awarded for completing the gem bundle of the Sun Haven Museum.

name: Nel'Vari Mana Infuser
description: An infusion crystal, capable of turning mana energy into convienent mana orbs.

name: Explorer's Trophy
description: A golden trophy, awarded for completing the exploration bundle of the Sun Haven Museum.

name: Combat Trophy
description: A golden trophy, awarded for completing the combat bundle of the Sun Haven museum.

name: Fishing Trophy
description: A golden trophy, awarded for completing the fishing bundle of the Sun Haven Museum.

name: Elven Barn
description: A home for your Elven farm animal friends.

name: Basic Shed
description: Will you store tools in it? Winter decorations? Excess snaccoon plushies?! The tantalizing storage possibilties are endless.

name: Floral Ladder
description: Either someone repurposed this ladder into a floral arrangement, or they accidentally left it in their garden.

name: Hay Filled Wheel Barrow
description: Piled high with crunchy hay, these are a classic farm decor mainstay.

name: Large Hay Pile
description: A large pile of hay, perfect for decorating any farm.

name: Small Hay Pile
description: A little pile of hay, perfect for decorating any farm.

name: Oranges Filled Wheelbarrow
description: Orange you glad this wheelbarrow is filled with oranges?

name: Standee Filled Hay
description: Jazz up those boring old piles of hay with some cute wooden standees.

name: Spring Aquarium
description: A silly little spring home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Summer Aquarium
description: A silly little summer home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Fall Aquarium
description: A silly little fall home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Winter Aquarium
description: A silly little winter home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Nel'Vari Aquarium
description: A silly little elven home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Withergate Aquarium
description: A silly little monster home for all the fish you've collected.

name: Crate Of Apples
description: How do you like THESE apples?!

name: Empty Crate
description: Just an empty old shipping crate.

name: Empty Wheelbarrow
description: It may be empty, but it carries something heavier than any physical load: the weight of potential.

name: Flower Planter
description: A planter boxed filled with little bitty baby flowers.

name: Milk Churn
description: Back in the old days, people used these things to make butter. These days, of course, we have more sophisticated methods of buttercraft, like magic tables.

name: Tin Bucket
description: A small bucket that can carry just about anything in it, though it looks to be empty now.

name: Withergate Barn Arch
description: An spooktacular arch that proves subtlety is the enemy of style.

name: Danger Poster
description: Danger: You are on a farm with KILLER style.

name: No Sailing Poster
description: This sign is sure to keep those pesky sailboats away.

name: Iron Feeding Trough
description: A sturdy trough that will hold a feast of animal feed for your barn animal buddies.

name: Red Oil Drum
description: You ever try keeping something in a barrel made out of haunted deadwood? It doesn't work so good. The Demons quickly adapted metal for their barrel-related needs.

name: Green Oil Drum
description: You ever try keeping something in a barrel made out of haunted deadwood? It doesn't work so good. The Demons quickly adapted metal for their barrel-related needs.

name: Blue Oil Drum
description: You ever try keeping something in a barrel made out of haunted deadwood? It doesn't work so good. The Demons quickly adapted metal for their barrel-related needs.

name: Barrel Cluster
description: What could be more fun than one barrel? A CLUSTER of barrels!

name: Worm Infested Apples
description: Oh, disgusting!! Someone infested the worms with a bunch of nasty apples!

name: Thorny Planter
description: A planter box full of delightfully stabby little plants.

name: Bitey Planter
description: A planter box full of ravenous snapper plants... with a taste for farmer!

name: Pumpkin Filled Wheelbarrow
description: Filled with the bounty of a pumpkin patch harvest... wait, is that one cackling?

name: Old Scythe
description: The blade is too thin to survive even one more sharpening. Now it's just a piece of decor... or junk, depending on your taste in interior decoration.

name: Empty Planter
description: Planting boxes are great for junior farmers. Naturally, a farmer of your skill has no use for this - it's still a cute decoration, though.

name: T Shaped Pipe
description: Behold, the greatest feat of Demonic engineering: Indoor plumbing!!

name: Thick Green Pipe
description: Bog water, swimming pool water, slime... these pipes are designed to handle it all.

name: Line of Pipes
description: A nice and orderly row of pipes. Just... don't ask where they go.

name: Elven Window
description: Nature is outside your window. Now, it can be ON your window, too.

name: Nel'Vari Barn Arch
description: Old oakwood, bent into an arch and festooned with deep forest vines and lillies.

name: Hanging Spool of Rope
description: A length of rope, kept nice and tidy for whenever it may be needed.

name: Rake
description: What kind of weird farming tool is this? It's like some kind of weird comb on a stick... what did the farmers of old use it for, you wonder.

name: Pirate Anchor
description: Her anchorin' days are over. Now she just makes a fine wall decoration.

name: Pirate Bed
description: The finest bed buried treasure can buy.

name: Pirate Cannon
description: A big ol' honkin' cannon... though it's only a replica and can't actually be fired. Too bad!

name: Pirate Chair
description: I didn't know chairs could be pirates. Arrrrr.

name: Pirate Chest
description: Don't get your hopes up - there's no lost treasure inside, it's just a cute decorative chest.

name: Pirate Hammock
description: An old piece of ship sail, repurposed into a primitive pirate hammock.

name: Pirate Treasure Map
description: A tattered treasure map, showing the location of a legendary pirate treasure. Too bad you were always bad at reading maps!

name: Pirate Wardrobe
description: Keep your spare peglegs organized and stored away in this barrel keg of a wardrobe.

name: Pirate Wood Post
description: Sturdy wooden posts that'll keep a ship tied to shore, so it doesn't float away in the waves!

name: Seaside Bed
description: She sleeps in seashells by the sea snore.

name: Seaside Chair
description: Sitting is great, but don't forget to stand up occasionally and stretch your fins.

name: Seaside Chest
description: Merfolk are great at restoring dingy old pirate treasure chests into cute little numbers like this one.

name: Seaside End Table
description: The only table you need while you kick back on a tropical seaside shore.

name: Seaside Lamp
description: It's hard to light a lantern under the sea (well, actually, it's sort of impossible). To adapt to life under the waves, the merfolk people use enchanted pearls that glow with light.

name: Seaside Table
description: Many a merfolk diplomatic debate (and tea party) has been had over tables like this.

name: Seaside Wardrobe
description: This fancy wardrobe is watertight up to 4,000 meters!

name: Blue Seaside Shell Rug
description: The world might be your oyster, but this clam can be your rug.

name: Blue Seaside Starfish Rug
description: Did you know that starfish can have as many as 15,000 suction cups across their body? Well, not this one, though. Because this one is a rug.

name: Pink Seaside Shell Rug
description: The world might be your oyster, but this clam can be your rug.

name: Pink Seaside Starfish Rug
description: Did you know that starfish can have as many as 15,000 suction cups across their body? Well, not this one, though. Because this one is a rug.

name: Mushroom Bed
description: Lay your head down on the velvety mushroom caps and dream your mushroomy dreams.

name: Mushroom Bookshelf
description: Filled with books and mushrooms. Mostly mushrooms, though.

name: Mushroom Carpet
description: A supple linen carpet, depicting adorable little mushrooms along its borders.

name: Mushroom Coat Rack
description: Someone hand carved little mushrooms to hang your coat on - how adorable!

name: Mushroom Table
description: Put your coffee, your mushrooms - or heck, even your mushroom coffee, on this thing.

name: Mushroom End Table
description: A little mushroom table. Mush room for everything you want to put on it, yes.

name: Red Mushroom Decoration
description: A clay mushroom created by skilled Elven clay workers - it looks shockingly lifelike!

name: Light Brown Mushroom Decoration
description: A clay mushroom created by skilled Elven clay workers - it looks shockingly lifelike!

name: Silo
description: Grain silos feed all animals on the same map, and store a LOT of animal feed... which means you can afford to own a LOT of animals! Once placed, remember to use a pickaxe to move it!

name: Chicken Coop
description: It's like a little house, but for chickens!

name: Basic Wooden Chair
description: Basic in style, but not in quality.

name: Spring Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of spring on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Summer Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of summer on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Fall Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of fall on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Winter Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of winter on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Dizzite
description: Gems like this aren't usually found in Sun Haven. Dizzy must have brought it here from another land.

name: Nel'Vari Butterfly Garden
description: A garden home for your moth farm animals. It will make them happy and lead to increased yields.

name: Monster Juicer
description: For turning monster crops into monster juice. Juices provide restorative properties.

name: Monster Crafting Table
description: A monstrous work bench outfitted with strange tools the likes you've never seen before.

name: Elven Crafting Table
description: An enchanted stump stocked with highly specialized Elven tools.

name: Elven Juicer
description: Turns Nel'Vari crops into juice - it works so well you'd swear it was magic! Juices provide restorative properties.

name: Woven Wood Fence
description: Elven wood that has been intricately woven together in a mesmerizingly beautiful yet sturdy fence.

name: Woven Wood Gate
description: Mere fence gates, though they're more beautiful than any door you've ever seen.

name: Glorite Mining Machine
description: Powered by coal or fire runes, this machine extracts mana energy from the earth and condenses it into crystals... but at what cost?

name: Mana Siphoner
description: Powered by coal or fire runes, this enchanted flower draws mana energy from the earth and condenses it into mana orbs.

name: Ticket Counterfeiter
description: A ticket printing machine made using stolen schematics. If Xyla ever gets her claws on the scum printing off their own tickets...

name: Ticket Counterfeiter Schematic
description: Rough drawings and instructions that detail how to construct a ticket printing machine.

name: Withergate Workshop Permit
description: Oh, it's an official permit for building your own workshop! It's even signed by "King Menos". How legitimate!

name: Greenhouse (Spring)
description: Funny, it doesn't look green.

name: Greenhouse (Summer)
description: Funny, it doesn't look green.

name: Greenhouse (Fall)
description: Funny, it doesn't look green.

name: Greenhouse (Winter)
description: Funny, it doesn't look green.

name: Nursery Crafting Table
description: A very special table with all the supplies you need to create a mountain of baby supplies... Trust us, you'll need them!

name: Butterfly Statue A
description: A bush, expertly trimmed into the shape of a beautiful butterfly.

name: Diamond Display
description: A hunk of diamond, the size of your head, cut into a breathtakingly beautiful shape. 'Nothing is too good for you' an inscription on the golden glasp reads.

name: Mini Duke Statue
description: A solid gold statue of Anne's most important business partner, her pet lizard Duke.

name: Witch's Moon
description: A notoriously difficult to cultivate herb that requires extensive knowledge of witchcraft, it's supposed to bring an air of peace wherever it is kept.

name: Dried Herbs
description: It looks like Catherine handmade this wooden rack just for you! The dried herbs are aromatic, and are meant to stink nice.

name: Elegant Bass
description: A beautiful bass cello, handcrafted by an artisan instrument maker who lived over a hundred years ago.

name: Golden Harp
description: Claude had this one-of-a-kind ultra-priceless collector's harp sitting around and figured you'd like it.

name: Witherknight Statue
description: Carved of solid witherstone, this imposing statue captures the form of a legendary hero in Demonic history, a Demon known only as 'The Witherknight'.

name: Red Stocking
description: Festive socks. Legends tell that if hung up, a fat red man will sometimes break into your house at night and leave stuff in them!

name: Wall Mounted Sword
description: In Demonic culture, swords are representations of lineage and power. The gifting of this sword is a recognition that the receiver is worthy to join the annals of Demonic history.

name: Donovan Town Flag
description: A blood-red banner, with a self-portrait of Donovan haphazardly taped across it. Castle Withergate has plenty of banners, they probably won't miss this one...

name: Tire Chair
description: There's NOTHING you CAN'T make out of old tires - Donovan

name: Luminesent Pumpkin
description: A little pumpkin that glows with pure mana. Iris enchanted it for a dear friend's birthday.

name: Glowing Flower Lights
description: An enchanted hanging vine that bears glowing yellow blossoms. Very Iris.

name: Young Bonsai
description: Jun has been cultivating this bonsai for years - just waiting for the perfect person to gift it to.

name: Woodblock Printed Scroll
description: A gorgeous print produced using ancient woodblock techniques, it's a rather valuable thing to turn into a gift.

name: Soggy Sandcastle
description: Kai thought he'd make you the perfect birthday present. Well, it's the thought that counts, right?

name: Snake Statue
description: A strange wave-washed statue of a snake creature. It looks like it was found deep underneath the waves.

name: Kitty's Birthday Dress
description: One of Kitty's most skillfully crafted dresses. It's much too pretty to risk wearing it, you may damage the seams!

name: Cat Scratching Post
description: Kitty's kittens love scratchy posts. Why not a farmer?

name: Auto-Mixer
description: A state of the art automatic mixer contraption, what a thoughtful (and pricey) gift!

name: Delicious Bread Display
description: A baker always has a foolproof gift to fall back on: fresh bread.

name: Flaming Book of Spells
description: A fiery book of fire mage incantations. You don't possess the skills to open the book without searing your fingers, though...

name: Conjured Brazier
description: Captured flame, burning eternally in a brazier that is... also made out of flame.

name: Moontouched Fountain
description: No, Lucius did not have permission to take this fountain from the temple.

name: Moontouched Mirror
description: Moon, moon, on the wall...

name: Model Train Set
description: A model of a train. Wait, this looks familiar... Is this the train you and Lynn rode into Sun Haven on? Lynn must have made this herself - what impeccable craftsmanship!

name: Delicate Hammer
description: A blacksmithing hammer made from the fragments of many failed pieces of armor forged by Lynn. Turning her failures into something beautiful is very poetic, though the hammer is only for show.

name: Angelic Floral Tea Pot
description: A smart arrangement of daisies, kept in a beautiful teapot.

name: Angelic Incense
description: Simmering shards of Everbeyond dust, it gives off an indescribable aroma.

name: Great Army Guard Banner
description: A banner of the Great Army guard division, Nathaniel technically shouldn't be giving this away - but it just looks so neat!

name: Hanging Shortsword
description: Nathaniel once used this sword to skewer four shadeclaws in a single poke. True story. However now this sword is only for show.

name: Honorific Katana
description: A peerless katana, ready to rend any foe like wheat. However, the sword must never be taken from its shrine - it is a lesson in restraint.

name: Watercolor Tiger Wall Scroll
description: Vibrant water color brush strokes bring to life a creeping tiger, powerful and prepared to strike.

name: Wall Hanging Necklace
description: A beautiful necklace, no doubt plucked by the wind from a distant land.

name: Enchanted Pinwheel
description: A simple pinwheel, an enchanted cloud keeps it in motion even when there in no wind.

name: Hand Carved Squirrel Statue
description: A squirrel, roughly cut from a block of wood. Did... Did Vivi use her daggers to carve this...?

name: Nature Chair
description: Birthday presents are easy, just go in the woods and find some stumps or something, call it a chair. - Vivi

name: Nel'Varian Translation Texts
description: Tome upon tome upon tome of handwritten notes penned by Wesley. Maybe someday you'll get around to studying them...

name: Elven Lore Tapestry
description: Woven from natural threads taken from forest vines, the tapestry depicts the legend of the Elven race's creation: born from a great tree.

name: Personal Med Kit
description: Even if there isn't a doctor in the house, you should be as prepared as possible for any medical emergency!

name: Medical Grade Microscope
description: Using a bunch of weird mirror magic, this curious mechanism can observe things super duper up close.

name: Entertainment Bar
description: One of the rules of life outside of a cave: be prepared to entertain guests.

name: Neon Sign
description: Created under the careful order of Xyla, there's definitely no mistaking her hand in this lamp's design.

name: Brinestone Statue
description: A depiction of a vicious hammerhead shark, carved from solid brinestone. Karish doesn't seem like one to collect art, though the subject matter definitely makes sense.

name: Deeplight Lamp
description: In the darkest reaches of the briney Deeps the only light you'll find is the soft illumination of bio-light lamps such as this one lighting up the dark fathoms.

name: Coral Compass
description: A golden compass, stuck in a chunk of colorful coral. It looks like something Zaria found on her corsair travels.

name: Deeps Treasure Map
description: A map of underwater landscapes, known as a bathymetric map. It leads to a lost treasure that Zaria has, naturally, already claimed for herself. Still, it's a neat map!

name: Bunny Couch
description: The cushions are extra-springy, like they're almost asking to be hopped on.

name: Bunny Table
description: A wooden table with little white bunnies painted onto it.

name: Bunny Lamp
description: Lighting doesn't get any cuter than this.

name: Bunny Side Table
description: The drawer handle is a little carrot, how cute!

name: Bunny Wardrobe
description: Ever seen a wardrobe with giant bunny ears? Well, now you have!

name: Small Money Bag
description: Jingles like music to your ears when you shake it.

name: Large Mana Tome
description: Bursting with mana!

name: Pizza Box
description: This pizza box says it serves 4. Well, all 4 me.

name: Orb
description: Contains an orb.

name: Ticket
description: A strange looking ticket.

name: Elven Health Book
description: An ancient tome of Elven script, detailing how to increase one's vitality.

name: Four Region's Thank You Letter
description: An official document from the Four Region's Postal Service (FRPS), thanking you for your help in fulfilling their postal duties.

name: Set Sail Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Set Sail DLC Pack!

name: Ocean Shores Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Ocean Shores DLC Pack!

name: Mushy Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Mushy DLC Pack!

name: Snaccoon Costume Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Snaccoon Costume DLC Pack!

name: Classical EDM Record
description: Nothing will get your feet going quite like this electric record.

name: Groovy Record
description: Groove on.

name: Waltz Record
description: Care for a dance?

name: Celtic Record
description: A selection of rousing instruments that is certain to get your blood pumping.

name: Golden Record Player Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Golden Record Player DLC Pack!

name: Sentimental Record
description: A sentimental arrangement with the power to move people and castles alike.

name: Withergate Mask Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Withergate Mask DLC Pack!

name: Pet Baby Tiger Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Pet Baby Tiger DLC Pack!

name: Pet Baby Dragon Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Pet Baby Dragon DLC Pack!

name: Sparkling Gear Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Sparkling Gear DLC Pack!

name: Sweet Mounts Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Sweet Mounts DLC Pack!

name: Wicked Mounts Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Wicked Mounts DLC Pack!

name: Dreamy Pet Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Dreamy Pet DLC Pack!

name: Spooky Pet Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Spooky Pet DLC Pack!

name: Spooky End Table
description: Haunted by the mournful soul of a deranged table lamp.

name: Spooky Bed
description: Sleep off the treats in this spooky bed.

name: Spooky Stack of Pumpkins
description: A stack of mini jack-o-lanterns, their pumpkiny visages crying out... for treats!

name: Spooky Table
description: Plenty of room for all  your spooky treats.

name: Spooky Couch
description: A couch can totally be spooky, if you attach enough pumpkins to it.

name: Spooky Chair
description: Sit In Peace.

name: Spooky Pumpkin Cauldron
description: A wicked pumpkin filled to the brim with bubbling pumpkin brew.

name: Spooky Rug
description: This rug is pumpkin-plush! That is to say it's made out of pumpkin.

name: Trick or Treat Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Trick or Treat DLC Pack!

name: Spooky Wardrobe
description: Maybe they should call it a WARLOCKdrobe, eh? ...I'll see myself out.

name: Spirit Petal Bed
description: You'll probably be pretty tired after conversing with the fae spirits, have a nap in this bed to recharge the ol' spiritual batteries.

name: Spirit Orb
description: Petals burn like ghostly wisps once plucked from the spirit realm in which they grow, in the overworld though, they simply float around.

name: Spirit Petal Wardrobe
description: A mystical wardrobe that magically links the physical realm to... the inside of a wardrobe.

name: Spirit Petal Rug
description: Intricately woven in tribute to the fae spirits.

name: Spirit Petal Chair
description: When sitting in this enchanted chair, you can almost hear the soflty twinkling bells of the fae spirits.

name: Spirit Petal Lamp
description: A lily flower lamp that emits a soft glow, attracting nearby fae spirits.

name: Spirit Petal Couch
description: Lilypads and lotus petals, the energy of fae spirits enchants them in a way no mortal enchanter could match.

name: Spirit Petal Table
description: Eating off of a giant lilypad isn't the easiest, but at least the flower blossom smells nice.

name: Spirit Petal Chest
description: A chest containing all the loot from the Spirit Petal DLC Pack!

name: Spirit Petal End Table
description: An end table for all your spirit fae-related stuff.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Black Guitar
description: When Demon engineers got their hands on guitars, they knew the instrument's design could do with a few... modifications.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Amp
description: Someone modified this bad boy to go all the way to 12.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Lamp
description: A lamp as metal as your taste in music.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Couch
description: Expensive red velvet cushions, ripped and stitched numerous times thanks to wild rock parties.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Black Rug
description: Absolutely brutal, especially by rug standards.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Red Guitar
description: When Demon engineers got their hands on guitars, they knew the instrument's design could do with a few... modifications.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Red Rug
description: Absolutely brutal, especially by rug standards.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Table
description: Pull up a chair, to the table... OF ROCK.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Wardrobe
description: The perfect place to leave your old concert outfits, empty record sleeves and dirty boots.

name: Rock 'n' Roll Gold Record Award
description: A record plated with pure gold! It doesn't play anymore, but it sure does look cool.
